Source: Allow functions defined in one script to be called by another script
en-us: Allow functions defined in one script to be called by another script
zh-cn: 允许一个脚本中定义的函数被其他脚本调用

Source: Causes the function assigned to OnInvoke to be called. Arguments passed to this function get passed to OnInvoke function.
en-us: Causes the function assigned to OnInvoke to be called. Arguments passed to this function get passed to OnInvoke function.
zh-cn: 调用指定给 OnInvoke 的函数。传递给此函数的参数将传给 OnInvoke 函数。

Source: Should be defined as a function. This function is called when Invoke() is called. Number of arguments is variable.
en-us: Should be defined as a function. This function is called when Invoke() is called. Number of arguments is variable.
zh-cn: 应定义为函数。此函数将在调用 Invoke() 时被调用。参数的数量是可变的。

Source: Allow events defined in one script to be subscribed to by another script
en-us: Allow events defined in one script to be subscribed to by another script
zh-cn: 允许一个脚本中定义的事件被其他脚本订阅

Source: Used to make the custom event fire (see Event for more info). Arguments can be variable length.
en-us: Used to make the custom event fire (see Event for more info). Arguments can be variable length.
zh-cn: 用于触发自定义事件（更多信息请参见 Event）。参数的长度是可变的。

Source: This event fires when the Fire() method is used.  Receives the variable length arguments from Fire().
en-us: This event fires when the Fire() method is used.  Receives the variable length arguments from Fire().
zh-cn: 此事件会在使用 Fire() 方法时触发。从 Fire() 接收可变长度参数。

Source: Used by networking and replication code to transmit touch events - no other purpose
en-us: Used by networking and replication code to transmit touch events - no other purpose
zh-cn: 在网络和复制代码中使用，用于传输触碰事件 — 无其他用途

Source: Prevents joint breakage from explosions, and stops Humanoids from taking damage
en-us: Prevents joint breakage from explosions, and stops Humanoids from taking damage
zh-cn: 阻止爆炸时的接头断开，以及阻止 Humanoid 受到伤害

Source: Allows players to seamlessly leave a game and join another
en-us: Allows players to seamlessly leave a game and join another
zh-cn: 允许玩家无缝地离开游戏并加入其他游戏

Source: Deprecated
en-us: Deprecated
zh-cn: 已过时

Source: A service which provides collections of instances based on tags assigned to them.
en-us: A service which provides collections of instances based on tags assigned to them.
zh-cn: 根据指定给实例的标记提供实例集合的服务。

Source: Deprecated. Use GetInstanceAddedSignal instead.
en-us: Deprecated. Use GetInstanceAddedSignal instead.
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 GetInstanceAddedSignal。

Source: Deprecated. Use GetInstancedRemovedSignal instead.
en-us: Deprecated. Use GetInstancedRemovedSignal instead.
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 GetInstancedRemovedSignal。

Source: Deprecated. Use GetTagged instead.
en-us: Deprecated. Use GetTagged instead.
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 GetTagged。

Source: Returns an array of all of the instances in the data model which have the given tag.
en-us: Returns an array of all of the instances in the data model which have the given tag.
zh-cn: 返回一个数据模型中拥有给定标记的所有实例的数组。

Source: Adds a tag to an instance.
en-us: Adds a tag to an instance.
zh-cn: 为实例添加标记。

Source: Removes a tag to an instance.
en-us: Removes a tag to an instance.
zh-cn: 为实例移除标记。

Source: Returns a list of all the collections that an instance belongs to.
en-us: Returns a list of all the collections that an instance belongs to.
zh-cn: 返回实例所属的所有集合的列表。

Source: Returns whether the given instance has the given tag.
en-us: Returns whether the given instance has the given tag.
zh-cn: 返回指定实例是否拥有指定标记。

Source: Returns a signal that fires when the given tag either has a new instance with that tag added to the data model or that tag is assigned to an instance within the data model.
en-us: Returns a signal that fires when the given tag either has a new instance with that tag added to the data model or that tag is assigned to an instance within the data model.
zh-cn: 当拥有指定标记的新实例被添加至数据模型，或该标记被指定给数据模型内的实例时，返回触发信号。

Source: Returns a signal that fires when the given tag either has an instance with that tag removed from the data model or that tag is removed from an instance within the data model.
en-us: Returns a signal that fires when the given tag either has an instance with that tag removed from the data model or that tag is removed from an instance within the data model.
zh-cn: 当拥有指定标记的实例被从数据模型中移除，或该标记被从数据模型内的实例上移除时，返回触发信号。

Source: A service used to set and get information about assets stored on the Roblox website.
en-us: A service used to set and get information about assets stored on the Roblox website.
zh-cn: 用于设置和获取 Roblox 网站上存储的资源相关信息的服务。

Source: Reverts a given place id to the version number provided. Returns true if successful on reverting, false otherwise.
en-us: Reverts a given place id to the version number provided. Returns true if successful on reverting, false otherwise.
zh-cn: 将指定场景 ID 恢复为提供的版本号。如果恢复成功则返回 true，否则返回 false。

Source: Sets the permissions for a placeID to the place accessType. An optional table (inviteList) can be included that will set the accessType for only the player names provided. The table should be set up as an array of usernames (strings).
en-us: Sets the permissions for a placeID to the place accessType. An optional table (inviteList) can be included that will set the accessType for only the player names provided. The table should be set up as an array of usernames (strings).
zh-cn: 设置一个 placeID 对场景 accessType 的许可。可以包含可选表（inviteList），以将 accessType 设为仅限提供的玩家名访问。可选表应设置为用户名（字符串）数组。

Source: Given a placeID, this function will return a table with the permissions of the place. Useful for determining what kind of permissions a particular user may have for a place.
en-us: Given a placeID, this function will return a table with the permissions of the place. Useful for determining what kind of permissions a particular user may have for a place.
zh-cn: 指定一个 placeID，此函数将返回该场景的许可表。常用于确认某个用户所拥有的某个场景的许可。

Source: Given a placeID, this function will return a table with the version info of the place. An optional arg of page number can be used to page through all revisions (a single page may hold about 50 revisions).
en-us: Given a placeID, this function will return a table with the version info of the place. An optional arg of page number can be used to page through all revisions (a single page may hold about 50 revisions).
zh-cn: 指定一个 placeID，此函数将返回该场景的版本信息表。可选的页面数量参数用于给所有版本分页 (单一页面可容纳约 50 个版本)。

Source: Given a creationID, this function will return the asset that created the creationID. If no other asset created the given creationID, 0 is returned.
en-us: Given a creationID, this function will return the asset that created the creationID. If no other asset created the given creationID, 0 is returned.
zh-cn: 指定一个 creationID，此函数将返回创建该 creationID 的资源。如果无其他资源创建指定 creationID ，则返回 0。

Source: Enabling http requests from scripts
en-us: Enabling http requests from scripts
zh-cn: 启用来自脚本的 http 请求

Source: Set ApiKey
en-us: Set ApiKey
zh-cn: 设置 ApiKey

Source: A service used to insert objects stored on the website into the game.
en-us: A service used to insert objects stored on the website into the game.
zh-cn: 用于将存储在网站上的对象插入至游戏中的服务。

Source: Can be set in non-filtering-enabled places to allow LoadAsset to be used in LocalScripts.
en-us: Can be set in non-filtering-enabled places to allow LoadAsset to be used in LocalScripts.
zh-cn: 可以在未启用过滤器的场景中设置，以允许在 LocalScript 中使用 LoadAsset。

Source: Allows free models to be inserted into place.
en-us: Allows free models to be inserted into place.
zh-cn: 允许将免费模型插入至场景。

Source: Returns a table for the assets stored in the category. A category is an setId from www.roblox.com that links to a set. More info on table format. More info on sets
en-us: Returns a table for the assets stored in the category. A category is an setId from www.roblox.com that links to a set. More info on table format. More info on sets
zh-cn: 返回一个存储在该类别中的资源表。类别为 www.roblox.com 上关联至一个集合的 setId。关于表格式的更多信息。关于集合的更多信息

Source: Inserts the Instance into the workspace.  It is recommended to use Instance.Parent = game.Workspace instead, as this can cause issues currently.
en-us: Inserts the Instance into the workspace.  It is recommended to use Instance.Parent = game.Workspace instead, as this can cause issues currently.
zh-cn: 将 Instance 插入至工作区。推荐改为使用 Instance.Parent = game.Workspace，因为此方法目前可能导致出现问题。

Source: Deprecated
en-us: Deprecated
zh-cn: 已过时

Source: Deprecated
en-us: Deprecated
zh-cn: 已过时

Source: Returns a table containing a list of the various setIds that are ROBLOX approved. More info on sets
en-us: Returns a table containing a list of the various setIds that are ROBLOX approved. More info on sets
zh-cn: 返回一个列举 ROBLOX 认可的多个 setId 的表。 关于集合的更多信息

Source: Returns a table containing a list of the various setIds that correspond to argument 'userId'. More info on sets
en-us: Returns a table containing a list of the various setIds that correspond to argument 'userId'. More info on sets
zh-cn: 返回一个列举与参数 'userId' 对应的多个 setId 的表。关于集合的更多信息

Source: Deprecated. Use GetBaseSets() instead.
en-us: Deprecated. Use GetBaseSets() instead.
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 GetBaseSets()。

Source: Deprecated. Use GetUserSets() instead.
en-us: Deprecated. Use GetUserSets() instead.
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 GetUserSets()。

Source: Returns a Model containing the Instance that resides at AssetId on the web. This call will also yield the script until the model is returned. Script execution can still continue, however, if you use a coroutine.
en-us: Returns a Model containing the Instance that resides at AssetId on the web. This call will also yield the script until the model is returned. Script execution can still continue, however, if you use a coroutine.
zh-cn: 返回一个包含驻留在网页上的 AssetId 中的 Instance 的 Model。此调用还会暂停脚本，直到返回该模型。但是，如果你使用协同程序，脚本仍可以继续执行。

Source: Similar to LoadAsset, but instead an AssetVersionId is passed in, which refers to a particular version of the asset which is not neccessarily the latest version.
en-us: Similar to LoadAsset, but instead an AssetVersionId is passed in, which refers to a particular version of the asset which is not neccessarily the latest version.
zh-cn: 与 LoadAsset 类似，但传入一个 AssetVersionId，引用一个特定的资源版本 (并非必须是最新版本)。

Source: Deprecated. Use WorldOrientation instead
en-us: Deprecated. Use WorldOrientation instead
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 WorldOrientation

Source: Euler angles applied in YXZ order
en-us: Euler angles applied in YXZ order
zh-cn: 以 YXZ 顺序应用的欧拉角

Source: Euler angles applied in YXZ order
en-us: Euler angles applied in YXZ order
zh-cn: 以 YXZ 顺序应用的欧拉角

Source: Primary axis. Corresponds to the LookVector, or the first column in the part-local Attachment CFrame rotation matrix
en-us: Primary axis. Corresponds to the LookVector, or the first column in the part-local Attachment CFrame rotation matrix
zh-cn: 主要轴线。对应于 LookVector，或部件本地 Attachment CFrame 旋转矩阵的第一列

Source: Secondary axis. Corresponds to the UpVector, or the second column in the part-local Attachment CFrame rotation matrix
en-us: Secondary axis. Corresponds to the UpVector, or the second column in the part-local Attachment CFrame rotation matrix
zh-cn: 次要轴线。对应于 UpVector，或部件本地 Attachment CFrame 旋转矩阵的第二列

Source: Primary axis in world space. Corresponds to the LookVector, or the first column in the world space Attachment CFrame rotation matrix.
en-us: Primary axis in world space. Corresponds to the LookVector, or the first column in the world space Attachment CFrame rotation matrix.
zh-cn: 世界空间中的主要轴线。对应于 LookVector，或世界空间 Attachment CFrame 旋转矩阵的第一列。

Source: Secondary axis in world space. Corresponds to the UpVector, or the second column in the world space Attachment CFrame rotation matrix.
en-us: Secondary axis in world space. Corresponds to the UpVector, or the second column in the world space Attachment CFrame rotation matrix.
zh-cn: 世界空间中的次要轴线。对应于 UpVector，或世界空间 Attachment CFrame 旋转矩阵的第二列

Source: Toggles whether or not this constraint is enabled. Disabled constraints will not render in game.
en-us: Toggles whether or not this constraint is enabled. Disabled constraints will not render in game.
zh-cn: 启用或禁用此约束。将不会在游戏中渲染被禁用的约束。

Source: The color of the in-game visual.
en-us: The color of the in-game visual.
zh-cn: 游戏内视觉效果的颜色。

Source: Toggles the in-game visual associated with this constraint.
en-us: Toggles the in-game visual associated with this constraint.
zh-cn: 开启或关闭与此约束相关的游戏内视觉效果。

Source: Read-only boolean, true if the Constraint is active in world.
en-us: Read-only boolean, true if the Constraint is active in world.
zh-cn: 只读布尔值，当 Constraint 在世界中启用时为 true。

Source: Enables the angular limit between the axis of Attachment0 and the axis of Attachment1.
en-us: Enables the angular limit between the axis of Attachment0 and the axis of Attachment1.
zh-cn: 启用 Attachment0 的轴线和 Attachment1 的轴线之间的角度限制。

Source: Maximum angle between the two main axes. Value in [0, 180].
en-us: Maximum angle between the two main axes. Value in [0, 180].
zh-cn: 两条主要轴线之间的最大角度。取值为 [0, 180]。

Source: Restitution of the limit, or how elastic it is. Value in [0, 1].
en-us: Restitution of the limit, or how elastic it is. Value in [0, 1].
zh-cn: 限制的弹性或弹性如何。取值为 [0, 1]。

Source: Enables the angular limits around the main axis of Attachment1.
en-us: Enables the angular limits around the main axis of Attachment1.
zh-cn: 启用与 Attachment1 的主要轴线相关的角度限制。

Source: Upper angular limit around the axis of Attachment1. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Upper angular limit around the axis of Attachment1. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: Attachment1 的轴线的上角限制。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: Lower angular limit around the axis of Attachment1. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Lower angular limit around the axis of Attachment1. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: Attachment1 的轴线的下角限制。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: Radius of the in-game visual. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Radius of the in-game visual. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 游戏内视觉效果的半径。取值为 [0, ∞)。

Source: The length of the rope or the maximum distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The length of the rope or the maximum distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 绳索的长度或两个附件之间的最大距离。取值为 [0, ∞)。

Source: Restitution of the rope, or how elastic it is. Value in [0, 1].
en-us: Restitution of the rope, or how elastic it is. Value in [0, 1].
zh-cn: 绳索的弹性或弹性如何。取值为 [0, 1]。

Source: Current distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Current distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 两个附件的当前距离。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The thickness of the in-game visual (diameter). Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The thickness of the in-game visual (diameter). Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 游戏内视觉效果的厚度 (直径)。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The length of the rod or the distance to be maintained between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The length of the rod or the distance to be maintained between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 杆的长度或两个附件之间需要维持的距离。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Current distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Current distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 两个附件的当前距离。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The thickness of the in-game visual (diameter). Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The thickness of the in-game visual (diameter). Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 游戏内视觉效果的厚度 (直径)。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Enables limits on the length of the spring.
en-us: Enables limits on the length of the spring.
zh-cn: 启用弹簧的长度限制。

Source: The stiffness parameter of the spring. Force is scaled based on distance from the free length. The units of this property are force / distance. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The stiffness parameter of the spring. Force is scaled based on distance from the free length. The units of this property are force / distance. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 弹簧的刚度参数。力度与自由长度的距离成正比。此属性的单位为力/距离。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The damping parameter of the spring. The force is scaled with respect to relative velocity. The units of this property are force / velocity. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The damping parameter of the spring. The force is scaled with respect to relative velocity. The units of this property are force / velocity. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 弹簧的阻尼参数。力度与相对速度关系成正比。此属性的单位为力/速度。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The distance (in studs) between the two attachments at which the spring exerts no stiffness force. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The distance (in studs) between the two attachments at which the spring exerts no stiffness force. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 弹簧失去刚性力度时两个附件之间的距离 (以格为单位)。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The maximum force that the spring can apply. Useful to prevent instabilities. The units are mass * studs / seconds^2. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The maximum force that the spring can apply. Useful to prevent instabilities. The units are mass * studs / seconds^2. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 弹簧可以施加的最大力度。可用于保持稳定。单位为质量 * 格/秒 ^2。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Maximum spring length, or the maxium distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Maximum spring length, or the maxium distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 最大弹簧长度，或两个附件之间的最大距离。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Minimum spring length, or the minimum distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Minimum spring length, or the minimum distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 最小弹簧长度，或两个附件之间的最小距离。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The radius of the in-game spring coil visual. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The radius of the in-game spring coil visual. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 游戏内弹簧线圈视觉效果的半径。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The thickness of the spring wire (diameter) in the in-game visual. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The thickness of the spring wire (diameter) in the in-game visual. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 游戏内视觉效果的弹簧线圈粗细 (直径)。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The number of coils in the in-game visual. Value in [0, 8].
en-us: The number of coils in the in-game visual. Value in [0, 8].
zh-cn: 游戏内视觉效果的线圈数量。取值为 [0, 8]。

Source: Current distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Current distance between the two attachments. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 两个附件的当前距离。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Read-only boolean, true if the joint is active in world. Rigid joints may be inactive if they are redundant or form cycles.
en-us: Read-only boolean, true if the joint is active in world. Rigid joints may be inactive if they are redundant or form cycles.
zh-cn: 只读布尔值，若接头在世界中处于使用状态则为 true。如果硬接头过剩或形成环形，则可能未使用。

Source: If true Part0 and Part1 will not collide, if false the parts will collide.
en-us: If true Part0 and Part1 will not collide, if false the parts will collide.
zh-cn: 取值为 true 时 Part0 和 Part1 不会碰撞，取值为 false 时则会产生碰撞。

Source: Type of the rotational actuator: None, Motor, or Servo.
en-us: Type of the rotational actuator: None, Motor, or Servo.
zh-cn: 旋转传动机构的类型: 无、电机或伺服。

Source: Enables the angular limits on rotations around the main axis of Attachment0.
en-us: Enables the angular limits on rotations around the main axis of Attachment0.
zh-cn: 启用围绕 Attachment0 的主要轴线的旋转角度限制。

Source: Upper limit for the angle from the SecondaryAxis of Attachment0 to the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Upper limit for the angle from the SecondaryAxis of Attachment0 to the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: Attachment0 的 SecondaryAxis 相对 Attachment1 的 SecondaryAxis 在旋转轴的角度上限。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: Lower limit for the angle from the SecondaryAxis of Attachment0 to the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Lower limit for the angle from the SecondaryAxis of Attachment0 to the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: Attachment0 的 SecondaryAxis 相对 Attachment1 的 SecondaryAxis 在旋转轴的角度下限。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: Restitution of the two limits, or how elastic they are. Value in [0,1].
en-us: Restitution of the two limits, or how elastic they are. Value in [0,1].
zh-cn: 两个限制的弹性或弹性如何。取值为 [0,1]。

Source: The target angular velocity of the motor in radians per second around the rotation axis. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The target angular velocity of the motor in radians per second around the rotation axis. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 电机的目标角速度，以绕旋转轴转动的弧度/秒为单位。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The maximum torque the motor can apply to achieve the target angular velocity. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The maximum torque the motor can apply to achieve the target angular velocity. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 电机为达到目标角速度可施加的最大扭矩。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The maximum angular acceleration of the motor in radians per second square. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The maximum angular acceleration of the motor in radians per second square. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 电机的最大角加速度，以弧度/秒^2 为单位。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Target angular speed. This value is unsigned as the servo will always move toward its target. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Target angular speed. This value is unsigned as the servo will always move toward its target. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 目标角速度。此值为不分正负的值，因为伺服总是在向目标移动。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Maximum torque the servo motor can apply. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Maximum torque the servo motor can apply. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 伺服电机可施加的最大扭矩。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Target angle for the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 from the SecondaryAxis of Attachment0 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Target angle for the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 from the SecondaryAxis of Attachment0 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: Attachment1 的 SecondaryAxis 相对 Attachment0 的 SecondaryAxis 在旋转轴的目标角度。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: Signed angle between the SecondaryAxis of Attchement0 and the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Signed angle between the SecondaryAxis of Attchement0 and the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: 旋转轴上 Attachment0 的 SecondaryAxis 和 Attachment1 的 SecondaryAxis 之间的有正负之分的角度。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: Radius of the in-game visual. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Radius of the in-game visual. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 游戏内视觉效果的半径。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Type of linear actuator (along the axis of the slider): None, Motor, or Servo.
en-us: Type of linear actuator (along the axis of the slider): None, Motor, or Servo.
zh-cn: 线性传动机构 (沿滚动条轴线) 的类型: 无、电机或伺服。

Source: Enables the limits on the linear motion along the axis of the slider.
en-us: Enables the limits on the linear motion along the axis of the slider.
zh-cn: 启用沿滚动条轴线的线性运动限制。

Source: Lower limit for the position of Attachment1 with respect to Attachment0 along the slider axis. Value in (-inf, inf).
en-us: Lower limit for the position of Attachment1 with respect to Attachment0 along the slider axis. Value in (-inf, inf).
zh-cn: Attachment1 相对 Attachment 0 沿滚动条轴线的位置下限。取值为 (-inf, inf)。

Source: Upper limit for the position of Attachment1 with respect to Attachment0 along the slider axis. Value in (-inf, inf).
en-us: Upper limit for the position of Attachment1 with respect to Attachment0 along the slider axis. Value in (-inf, inf).
zh-cn: Attachment1 相对 Attachment 0 沿滚动条轴线的位置上限。取值为 (-inf, inf)。

Source: Restitution of the two limits, or how elastic they are. Value in [0, 1].
en-us: Restitution of the two limits, or how elastic they are. Value in [0, 1].
zh-cn: 两个限制的弹性或弹性如何。取值为 [0, 1]。

Source: The target linear velocity of the motor in studs per second along the slider axis. Value in (-inf, inf).
en-us: The target linear velocity of the motor in studs per second along the slider axis. Value in (-inf, inf).
zh-cn: 电机沿滚动条轴线的目标线性速度，以格/秒为单位。取值为 (-inf, inf)。

Source: The maximum force the motor can apply to achieve the target velocity. Units are mass * studs / seconds^2. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The maximum force the motor can apply to achieve the target velocity. Units are mass * studs / seconds^2. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 电机为达到目标速度可施加的最大力度。单位为质量*格/秒 ^2。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The maximum acceleration of the motor in studs per second squared. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The maximum acceleration of the motor in studs per second squared. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 电机的最大加速度，以格/秒^2 为单位。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Target speed in studs per second. This value is unsigned as the servo will always move toward its target. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Target speed in studs per second. This value is unsigned as the servo will always move toward its target. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 目标速度，以格/秒为单位。此值为不分正负的值，因为伺服总是在向目标移动。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Maximum force the servo motor can apply. Units are mass * studs / seconds^2. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Maximum force the servo motor can apply. Units are mass * studs / seconds^2. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 伺服电机可施加的最大力度。单位为质量 * 格/秒^2。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Target position of Attachment1 with respect to Attachment0 along the slider axis. Value in (-inf, inf).
en-us: Target position of Attachment1 with respect to Attachment0 along the slider axis. Value in (-inf, inf).
zh-cn: 沿滚动条轴线上 Attachment1 相对 Attachment0 的目标位置。取值为 (-inf, inf)。

Source: Current position of Attachment1 with respect to Attachment0 along the slider axis. Value in (-inf, inf).
en-us: Current position of Attachment1 with respect to Attachment0 along the slider axis. Value in (-inf, inf).
zh-cn: 沿滚动条轴线上 Attachment1 相对 Attachment0 的当前位置。取值为 (-inf, inf)。

Source: Size of the in-game visual associated with this constraint. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Size of the in-game visual associated with this constraint. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 与此约束关联的游戏内视觉效果的大小。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Direction of the rotation axis as an angle from the x-axis in the xy-plane of Attachment0. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Direction of the rotation axis as an angle from the x-axis in the xy-plane of Attachment0. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: 旋转轴的方向与 Attachment0 的 xy 平面上的 x 轴形成的夹角。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: Type of angular actuator: None, Motor, or Servo.
en-us: Type of angular actuator: None, Motor, or Servo.
zh-cn: 角传动机构的类型: 无、电机、伺服。

Source: Enables the angular limits around the rotation axis.
en-us: Enables the angular limits around the rotation axis.
zh-cn: 启用围绕旋转轴线的角度限制。

Source: Upper limit for the angle (in degrees) between the reference axis and the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Upper limit for the angle (in degrees) between the reference axis and the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: 参考轴线和 Attachment1 的 SecondaryAxis 围绕旋转轴的角度上限 (以度为单位)。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: Lower limit for the angle (in degrees) between the reference axis and the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Lower limit for the angle (in degrees) between the reference axis and the SecondaryAxis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: 参考轴线和 Attachment1 的 SecondaryAxis 围绕旋转轴的角度下限 (以度为单位)。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: Restitution of the two limits, or how elastic they are. Value in [0, 1].
en-us: Restitution of the two limits, or how elastic they are. Value in [0, 1].
zh-cn: 两个限制的弹性或弹性如何。取值为 [0, 1]。

Source: The target angular velocity of the motor in radians per second around the rotation axis. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The target angular velocity of the motor in radians per second around the rotation axis. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 电机的目标角速度，以绕旋转轴转动的弧度/秒为单位。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The maximum torque the motor can apply to achieve the target angular velocity. The units are mass * studs^2 / second^2. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The maximum torque the motor can apply to achieve the target angular velocity. The units are mass * studs^2 / second^2. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 电机为达到目标角速度可施加的最大扭矩。单位为质量 * 格^2/秒^2。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: The maximum angular acceleration of the motor in radians per second squared. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: The maximum angular acceleration of the motor in radians per second squared. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 电机的最大角加速度，以弧度/秒^2为单位。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Target angular speed. This value is unsigned as the servo will always move toward its target. In radians per second. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Target angular speed. This value is unsigned as the servo will always move toward its target. In radians per second. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 目标角速度。此值为不分正负的值，因为伺服总是在向目标移动。以弧度/秒^2为单位。。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Maximum torque the servo motor can apply. The units are mass * studs^2 / second^2. Value in [0, inf).
en-us: Maximum torque the servo motor can apply. The units are mass * studs^2 / second^2. Value in [0, inf).
zh-cn: 伺服电机可施加的最大扭矩。单位为质量 * 格^2/秒^2。取值为 [0, inf)。

Source: Target angle (in degrees) between the reference axis and the secondary axis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Target angle (in degrees) between the reference axis and the secondary axis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: 参考轴线与 Attachment1 的次要轴线围绕旋转轴的目标角度 (以度为单位)。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: Signed angle (in degrees) between the reference axis and the secondary axis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
en-us: Signed angle (in degrees) between the reference axis and the secondary axis of Attachment1 around the rotation axis. Value in [-180, 180].
zh-cn: 参考轴线与 Attachment1 的次要轴线围绕旋转轴的有正负之分的角度 (以度为单位)。取值为 [-180, 180]。

Source: The unit vector direction of the rotation axis in world coordinates.
en-us: The unit vector direction of the rotation axis in world coordinates.
zh-cn: 旋转轴在世界坐标中的单位矢量方向。

Source: Enable the visibility of the rotation axis.
en-us: Enable the visibility of the rotation axis.
zh-cn: 启用旋转轴的可见性。

Source: Used to receive input from the user. Actually tracks mouse events and keyboard events.
en-us: Used to receive input from the user. Actually tracks mouse events and keyboard events.
zh-cn: 用于接收用户输入。实际追踪鼠标事件和键盘事件。

Source: The CoordinateFrame of where the Mouse ray is currently hitting a 3D object in the Workspace.  If the mouse is not over any 3D objects in the Workspace, this property is nil.
en-us: The CoordinateFrame of where the Mouse ray is currently hitting a 3D object in the Workspace.  If the mouse is not over any 3D objects in the Workspace, this property is nil.
zh-cn: Mouse 光线在工作区中当前指向的 3D 物体的 CoordinateFrame。若鼠标在工作区中未指向任意 3D 物体，则此属性无值。

Source: The current Texture of the Mouse Icon. Stored as a string, for more information on how to format the string go here
en-us: The current Texture of the Mouse Icon. Stored as a string, for more information on how to format the string go here
zh-cn: Mouse Icon 的当前 Texture。以字符串形式存储，欲了解更多关于该字符串的格式信息，请点击这里

Source: The CoordinateFrame of where the Mouse is when the mouse is not clicking.  This CoordinateFrame will be very close to the Camera.CoordinateFrame.
en-us: The CoordinateFrame of where the Mouse is when the mouse is not clicking.  This CoordinateFrame will be very close to the Camera.CoordinateFrame.
zh-cn: 鼠标未点击时 Mouse 所在位置的 CoordinateFrame。此 CoordinateFrame 会与 Camera.CoordinateFrame 非常接近。

Source: The Part the mouse is currently over. If the mouse is not currently over any object (on the skybox, for example) this property is nil.
en-us: The Part the mouse is currently over. If the mouse is not currently over any object (on the skybox, for example) this property is nil.
zh-cn: 鼠标当前悬停位置的 Part。若鼠标当前未悬停在任意物体上方 (如在天空盒上)，则此属性无值。

Source: A Part or Model that the Mouse will ignore when trying to find the Target, TargetSurface and Hit.
en-us: A Part or Model that the Mouse will ignore when trying to find the Target, TargetSurface and Hit.
zh-cn: Mouse 在尝试寻找 Target、TargetSurface 和 Hit 时会忽略的 Part 或 Model。

Source: The NormalId (Top, Left, Down, etc.) of the face of the part the Mouse is currently over.
en-us: The NormalId (Top, Left, Down, etc.) of the face of the part the Mouse is currently over.
zh-cn: 鼠标当前悬停位置的部件的面的 NormalId (Top、Left、Down 等)。

Source: The Unit Ray from where the mouse is (Origin) to the current Mouse.Target.
en-us: The Unit Ray from where the mouse is (Origin) to the current Mouse.Target.
zh-cn: 鼠标所在位置 (原来) 相对当前 Mouse.Target 的 Unit Ray。

Source: The viewport's (game window) width in pixels.
en-us: The viewport's (game window) width in pixels.
zh-cn: 观察窗 (游戏窗口) 的宽度，以像素为单位。

Source: The viewport's (game window) height in pixels.
en-us: The viewport's (game window) height in pixels.
zh-cn: 观察窗 (游戏窗口) 的高度，以像素为单位。

Source: The absolute pixel position of the Mouse along the x-axis of the viewport (game window). Values start at 0 on the left hand side of the screen and increase to the right.
en-us: The absolute pixel position of the Mouse along the x-axis of the viewport (game window). Values start at 0 on the left hand side of the screen and increase to the right.
zh-cn: Mouse 在观察窗 (游戏窗口) 的 x 轴上的绝对像素位置。屏幕最左侧取值为 0 并向右逐渐增加。

Source: The absolute pixel position of the Mouse along the y-axis of the viewport (game window). Values start at 0 on the top of the screen and increase to the bottom.
en-us: The absolute pixel position of the Mouse along the y-axis of the viewport (game window). Values start at 0 on the top of the screen and increase to the bottom.
zh-cn: Mouse 在观察窗 (游戏窗口) 的 y 轴上的绝对像素位置。屏幕最上部取值为 0 并向下逐渐增加。

Source: Fired when the first button (usually the left, but could be another) on the mouse is depressed.
en-us: Fired when the first button (usually the left, but could be another) on the mouse is depressed.
zh-cn: 按下鼠标上的第一个按钮 (通常为左键，但也有可能是右键) 时触发。

Source: Fired when the first button (usually the left, but could be another) on the mouse is release.
en-us: Fired when the first button (usually the left, but could be another) on the mouse is release.
zh-cn: 释放鼠标上的第一个按钮 (通常为左键，但也有可能是右键) 时触发。

Source: This event is currently non-operational.
en-us: This event is currently non-operational.
zh-cn: 此事件当前无法使用。

Source: This event is currently non-operational.
en-us: This event is currently non-operational.
zh-cn: 此事件当前无法使用。

Source: Fired constantly when the mouse is not firing any other event (i.e. the mouse isn't moving, nor any buttons being pressed or depressed).
en-us: Fired constantly when the mouse is not firing any other event (i.e. the mouse isn't moving, nor any buttons being pressed or depressed).
zh-cn: 鼠标未触发其他事件 (如鼠标未移动，且未按压或松开任意按钮) 时持续触发。

Source: Fired when a user presses a key on the keyboard. Argument is a string representation of the key.  If the key has no string representation (such as space), the string passed in is the keycode for that character. Keycodes are currently in ASCII.
en-us: Fired when a user presses a key on the keyboard. Argument is a string representation of the key.  If the key has no string representation (such as space), the string passed in is the keycode for that character. Keycodes are currently in ASCII.
zh-cn: 用户按下键盘上的一个按键时触发。参数为代表该按键的字符串。若该按键无代表字符串 (如空格)，则传入的字符串为该字符的按键代码。目前按键代码为 ASCII 格式。

Source: Fired when a user releases a key on the keyboard. Argument is a string representation of the key.  If the key has no string representation (such as space), the string passed in is the keycode for that character. Keycodes are currently in ASCII.
en-us: Fired when a user releases a key on the keyboard. Argument is a string representation of the key.  If the key has no string representation (such as space), the string passed in is the keycode for that character. Keycodes are currently in ASCII.
zh-cn: 当用户松开键盘上的一个按键时触发。参数为代表该按键的字符串。若该按键无代表字符串（如空格），则传入的字符串为该字符的键码。目前键码为 ASCII 格式。

Source: Fired when the mouse X or Y member changes.
en-us: Fired when the mouse X or Y member changes.
zh-cn: 鼠标的 X 或 Y 值改变时触发。

Source: This event is currently non-operational.
en-us: This event is currently non-operational.
zh-cn: 此事件当前无法使用。

Source: This event is currently non-operational.
en-us: This event is currently non-operational.
zh-cn: 此事件当前无法使用。

Source: Deprecated
en-us: Deprecated
zh-cn: 已过时

Source: Raises mouse events for parent object
en-us: Raises mouse events for parent object
zh-cn: 为父对象引发鼠标事件

Source: The maximum distance a Player's character can be from the ClickDetector's parent Part that will allow the Player's mouse to fire events on this object.
en-us: The maximum distance a Player's character can be from the ClickDetector's parent Part that will allow the Player's mouse to fire events on this object.
zh-cn: Player 的角色与 ClickDetector 的父系 Part 的最大距离，将允许 Player 的鼠标在该对象上触发事件。

Source: Fired when a player clicks on the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.
en-us: Fired when a player clicks on the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.
zh-cn: 玩家单击 ClickDetector 的父系 Part 时触发。提供的参数始终为 Player 类型。

Source: Fired when a player's mouse enters on the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.
en-us: Fired when a player's mouse enters on the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.
zh-cn: 玩家的鼠标进入 ClickDetector 的父系 Part 时触发。提供的参数始终为 Player 类型。

Source: Fired when a player's mouse leaves the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.
en-us: Fired when a player's mouse leaves the parent Part of ClickDetector. The argument provided is always of type Player.
zh-cn: 玩家的鼠标离开 ClickDetector 的父系 Part 时触发。提供的参数始终为 Player 类型。

Source: Makes the parent part or model object emit smoke
en-us: Makes the parent part or model object emit smoke
zh-cn: 使父部件或模型对象发出烟雾

Source: Makes two attachments emit trail when moving
en-us: Makes two attachments emit trail when moving
zh-cn: 使两个附件在移动时留下轨迹

Source: Makes beam between two attachments
en-us: Makes beam between two attachments
zh-cn: 在两个附件之间制造光束

Source: A generic particle system.
en-us: A generic particle system.
zh-cn: 一套通用粒子系统。

Source: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the particle emmitter. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.
en-us: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the particle emmitter. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.
zh-cn: 指定照明对粒子发射器的影响量。取值 0 表示完全熄灭，取值 1 表示完全点亮。中间的分数值表示从完全熄灭到完全点亮之间的状态。

Source: Makes the parent part or model object fantastic
en-us: Makes the parent part or model object fantastic
zh-cn: 使父部件或模型对象变得非常酷炫

Source: Creates an Explosion! This can be used as a purely graphical effect, or can be made to damage objects.
en-us: Creates an Explosion! This can be used as a purely graphical effect, or can be made to damage objects.
zh-cn: 制造一场爆炸! 可用于纯粹的图形效果，或用于破坏物体。

Source: How much force this Explosion exerts on objects within it's BlastRadius. Setting this to 0 creates a purely graphical effect. A larger number will cause Parts to fly away at higher velocities.
en-us: How much force this Explosion exerts on objects within it's BlastRadius. Setting this to 0 creates a purely graphical effect. A larger number will cause Parts to fly away at higher velocities.
zh-cn: 爆炸对在其 BlastRadius 内的物体施加的力度大小。设置为 0 可制造出纯粹的图形效果。数值越大，Part 被吹飞的速度就越快。

Source: How big the Explosion is. This is a circle starting from the center of the Explosion's Position, the larger this property the larger the circle of destruction.
en-us: How big the Explosion is. This is a circle starting from the center of the Explosion's Position, the larger this property the larger the circle of destruction.
zh-cn: 爆炸的范围大小。这是一个以爆炸位置中心为中心的圆，属性值越大，破坏圈就越大。

Source: Where the Explosion occurs in absolute world coordinates.
en-us: Where the Explosion occurs in absolute world coordinates.
zh-cn: 爆炸发生位置的绝对世界坐标。

Source: Defines the behavior of the Explosion. More info
en-us: Defines the behavior of the Explosion. More info
zh-cn: 定义 Explosion 的行为。更多信息

Source: Makes the parent part or model object emit fire
en-us: Makes the parent part or model object emit fire
zh-cn: 使父部件或模型对象喷出火焰

Source: The color of the base of the fire.  See SecondaryColor for more.
en-us: The color of the base of the fire.  See SecondaryColor for more.
zh-cn: 火焰的底色。更多信息请参阅 SecondaryColor。

Source: How hot the fire appears to be. The flame moves quicker the higher this value is set.
en-us: How hot the fire appears to be. The flame moves quicker the higher this value is set.
zh-cn: 火焰的热度。此值设置得越高，火焰移动的速度越快。

Source: The color the fire interpolates to from Color. The longer a particle exists in the fire, the close to this color it becomes.
en-us: The color the fire interpolates to from Color. The longer a particle exists in the fire, the close to this color it becomes.
zh-cn: 火焰与 Color 的插值颜色。粒子在火焰中存在得越久，它与此颜色就越接近。

Source: How large the fire appears to be.
en-us: How large the fire appears to be.
zh-cn: 火焰的大小。

Source: Equivalent to a seat, except that the character stands up rather than sits down.
en-us: Equivalent to a seat, except that the character stands up rather than sits down.
zh-cn: 等同于座位，但角色在起立而非坐下状态时除外。

Source: Automatically finds and powers hinge joints in an assembly.  Ignores motors.
en-us: Automatically finds and powers hinge joints in an assembly.  Ignores motors.
zh-cn: 自动在装配中寻找铰链接头并为其供能。请忽略电机。

Source: If someone is carrying this flag, this bool determines whether or not they can drop it and run.
en-us: If someone is carrying this flag, this bool determines whether or not they can drop it and run.
zh-cn: 若有人携带此旗帜，此布尔值将决定他们是否可以抛弃旗帜并跑开。

Source: The Team this flag is for. Corresponds with the TeamColors in the Teams service.
en-us: The Team this flag is for. Corresponds with the TeamColors in the Teams service.
zh-cn: 此旗帜所属的 Team。对应 Teams 服务中的 TeamColors。

Source: Descibes a texture that is placed on one of the sides of the Part it is parented to.
en-us: Descibes a texture that is placed on one of the sides of the Part it is parented to.
zh-cn: 描述放在其所属 Part 的一个面上的纹理。

Source: Describes the face of the Part the decal will be applied to. More info
en-us: Describes the face of the Part the decal will be applied to. More info
zh-cn: 描述该贴花将会应用在 Part 哪个面。更多信息

Source: How much light will appear to reflect off of the decal.
en-us: How much light will appear to reflect off of the decal.
zh-cn: 贴花所反射的照明量。

Source: How light will react to the surface of the decal.
en-us: How light will react to the surface of the decal.
zh-cn: 照明对贴花表面的反应。

Source: How visible the decal is.  1 is completely invisible, while 0 is completely opaque
en-us: How visible the decal is.  1 is completely invisible, while 0 is completely opaque
zh-cn: 贴花的可见度。1 为完全不可见，0 为完全不透明。

Source: Read-only boolean, true if the joint is active in world. Rigid joints may be inactive if they are redundant or form cycles.
en-us: Read-only boolean, true if the joint is active in world. Rigid joints may be inactive if they are redundant or form cycles.
zh-cn: 只读布尔值，若接头在世界中处于使用状态则为 true。如果硬接头过剩或形成环形，则可能未使用。

Source: Stores a int value in it's Value member. Useful to share int information across multiple scripts.
en-us: Stores a int value in it's Value member. Useful to share int information across multiple scripts.
zh-cn: 在其 Value 成员中存储一个整数值。用于在多个脚本之间共享整数信息。

Source: Stores a Ray value in it's Value member. Useful to share Ray information across multiple scripts.
en-us: Stores a Ray value in it's Value member. Useful to share Ray information across multiple scripts.
zh-cn: 在其 Value 成员中存储一个 Ray 值。用于在多个脚本之间共享 Ray 信息。

Source: Stores an int value in it's Value member.  Value is clamped to be in range of Min and MaxValue. Useful to share int information across multiple scripts.
en-us: Stores an int value in it's Value member.  Value is clamped to be in range of Min and MaxValue. Useful to share int information across multiple scripts.
zh-cn: 在其 Value 成员中存储一个整数值。该值被限制在 MinValue 和 MaxValue 之间。用于在多个脚本之间共享整数信息。

Source: The maximum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set higher than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MaxValue
en-us: The maximum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set higher than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MaxValue
zh-cn: 我们允许此 Value 设置的最大值。若 Value 高于此值，将会自动被调整为 MaxValue。

Source: The minimum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set lower than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MinValue
en-us: The minimum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set lower than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MinValue
zh-cn: 我们允许此 Value 设置的最小值。若 Value 低于此值，将会自动被调整为 MinValue。

Source: Stores a double value in it's Value member.  Value is clamped to be in range of Min and MaxValue. Useful to share double information across multiple scripts.
en-us: Stores a double value in it's Value member.  Value is clamped to be in range of Min and MaxValue. Useful to share double information across multiple scripts.
zh-cn: 在其 Value 成员中存储一个双精度值。该值被限制在 MinValue 和 MaxValue 之间。用于在多个脚本之间共享双精度信息。

Source: The maximum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set higher than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MaxValue
en-us: The maximum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set higher than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MaxValue
zh-cn: 我们允许此 Value 设置的最大值。若 Value 高于此值，将会自动被调整为 MaxValue。

Source: The minimum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set lower than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MinValue
en-us: The minimum we allow this Value to be set.  If Value is set lower than this, it automatically gets adjusted to MinValue
zh-cn: 我们允许此 Value 设置的最小值。若 Value 低于此值，将会自动被调整为 MinValue。

Source: Stores a boolean value in it's Value member. Useful to share boolean information across multiple scripts.
en-us: Stores a boolean value in it's Value member. Useful to share boolean information across multiple scripts.
zh-cn: 在其 Value 成员中存储一个布尔值。用于在多个脚本之间共享布尔信息。

Source: Renders a thin cylinder than can be adorned with textures that 'flow' from one object to the next. Has basic pathing abilities and attempts to to not intersect anything. More info
en-us: Renders a thin cylinder than can be adorned with textures that 'flow' from one object to the next. Has basic pathing abilities and attempts to to not intersect anything. More info
zh-cn: 渲染一个可以使用从一个物体“流”向下一个物体的纹理进行装饰的细圆柱体。拥有基本的寻路能力且试图不与任何东西相交。更多信息

Source: Controls how the decals are positioned along the wire. More info
en-us: Controls how the decals are positioned along the wire. More info
zh-cn: 控制贴花在线上的定位方式。更多信息

Source: The object the FloorWire 'emits' from
en-us: The object the FloorWire 'emits' from
zh-cn: “发射”出 FloorWire 的物体

Source: The space between two textures on the wire. Note: studs are relative depending on how far the camera is from the FloorWire.
en-us: The space between two textures on the wire. Note: studs are relative depending on how far the camera is from the FloorWire.
zh-cn: 线上两个纹理之间的空间。注: 格的相对大小取决于镜头与 FloorWire之间的距离。

Source: The image we use to render the textures that flow from beginning to end of the FloorWire.
en-us: The image we use to render the textures that flow from beginning to end of the FloorWire.
zh-cn: 我们用来渲染从 FloorWire 头部流向尾部的纹理的图像。

Source: The size in studs of the Texture we use to flow from one object to the next.
en-us: The size in studs of the Texture we use to flow from one object to the next.
zh-cn: 我们用来从一个物体流向下一个物体的纹理的大小 (以格为单位)。

Source: The object the FloorWire 'emits' to
en-us: The object the FloorWire 'emits' to
zh-cn: FloorWire “发射”出的物体

Source: The rate of travel that the textures flow along the wire.
en-us: The rate of travel that the textures flow along the wire.
zh-cn: 纹理沿线流动的速度。

Source: How thick the wire is.
en-us: How thick the wire is.
zh-cn: 线的厚度。

Source: Stores a CFrame value in it's Value member. Useful to share CFrame information across multiple scripts.
en-us: Stores a CFrame value in it's Value member. Useful to share CFrame information across multiple scripts.
zh-cn: 在其 Value 成员中存储一个 CFrame 值。用于在多个脚本之间共享 CFrame 信息。

Source: Stores a Color3 value in it's Value member. Useful to share Color3 information across multiple scripts.
en-us: Stores a Color3 value in it's Value member. Useful to share Color3 information across multiple scripts.
zh-cn: 在其 Value 成员中存储一个 Color3 值。用于在多个脚本之间共享 Color3 信息。

Source: Stores a BrickColor value in it's Value member. Useful to share BrickColor information across multiple scripts.
en-us: Stores a BrickColor value in it's Value member. Useful to share BrickColor information across multiple scripts.
zh-cn: 在其 Value 成员中存储一个 BrickColor 值。用于在多个脚本之间共享 BrickColor 信息。

Source: The base class to all Value Objects.
en-us: The base class to all Value Objects.
zh-cn: 所有 Value 对象的基类。

Source: Deprecated. Use Play() instead
en-us: Deprecated. Use Play() instead
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 Play()

Source: The sound will play when it is removed from the Workspace. Looped sounds don't play
en-us: The sound will play when it is removed from the Workspace. Looped sounds don't play
zh-cn: 从工作区中移除时将会播放音效。不会播放循环音效

Source: An echo audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
en-us: An echo audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
zh-cn: 可应用于 Sound 或 SoundGroup 的回声音频效果。

Source: A Flanging audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
en-us: A Flanging audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
zh-cn: 可应用于 Sound 或 SoundGroup 的镶边音频效果。

Source: A Distortion audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
en-us: A Distortion audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
zh-cn: 可应用于 Sound 或 SoundGroup 的失真音频效果。

Source: A Pitch Shifting audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
en-us: A Pitch Shifting audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
zh-cn: 可应用于 Sound 或 SoundGroup 的变调音频效果。

Source: A Chorus audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
en-us: A Chorus audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
zh-cn: 可应用于 Sound 或 SoundGroup 的合奏音频效果。

Source: A Tremolo audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
en-us: A Tremolo audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
zh-cn: 可应用于 Sound 或 SoundGroup 的颤音音频效果。

Source: A Reverb audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
en-us: A Reverb audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
zh-cn: 可应用于 Sound 或 SoundGroup 的混响音频效果。

Source: An Three-band Equalizer audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
en-us: An Three-band Equalizer audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
zh-cn: 可应用于 Sound 或 SoundGroup 的三波段均衡器音频效果。

Source: A Compressor audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
en-us: A Compressor audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.
zh-cn: 可应用于 Sound 或 SoundGroup 的压缩器音频效果。

Source: The ambient sound environment.  May not work when using hardware sound
en-us: The ambient sound environment.  May not work when using hardware sound
zh-cn: 环境声音环境。使用硬件声音时可能无法正常工作

Source: The doppler scale is a general scaling factor for how much the pitch varies due to doppler shifting in 3D sound. Doppler is the pitch bending effect when a sound comes towards the listener or moves away from it, much like the effect you hear when a train goes past you with its horn sounding. With dopplerscale you can exaggerate or diminish the effect.
en-us: The doppler scale is a general scaling factor for how much the pitch varies due to doppler shifting in 3D sound. Doppler is the pitch bending effect when a sound comes towards the listener or moves away from it, much like the effect you hear when a train goes past you with its horn sounding. With dopplerscale you can exaggerate or diminish the effect.
zh-cn: 多布勒标度是用于衡量 3D 音效中因多布勒频移而导致的音调变化程度的一种通用衡量因素。多普勒效应是指音源向聆听者移动或远离聆听者时所产生的音调变化，如火车从你身边经过的同时鸣笛所产生的效果。通过多普勒标度，你可以夸大或减弱这种效果。

Source: the relative distance factor, compared to 1.0 meters.
en-us: the relative distance factor, compared to 1.0 meters.
zh-cn: 相对距离因子，比照 1.0 米。

Source: Setting this value makes the sound drop off faster or slower. The higher the value, the faster volume will attenuate, and conversely the lower the value, the slower it will attenuate. For example a rolloff factor of 1 will simulate the real world, where as a value of 2 will make sounds attenuate 2 times quicker.
en-us: Setting this value makes the sound drop off faster or slower. The higher the value, the faster volume will attenuate, and conversely the lower the value, the slower it will attenuate. For example a rolloff factor of 1 will simulate the real world, where as a value of 2 will make sounds attenuate 2 times quicker.
zh-cn: 设置此值可以加快或减慢音量降低的速度。数值越大，音量衰减越快，数值越小，音量衰减越慢。例如，下降率为 1 时为模拟真实世界效果，而数值为 2 时则音量衰减速度将加快一倍。

Source: When SortOrder is set to Custom, this lua function is used to determine the ordering of elements. Function should take two arguments (each will be an Instance child to compare), and return true if a comes before b, otherwise return false. In other words, use this function the same way you would use a table.sort function. The sorting should be deterministic, otherwise sort will fail and fall back to name order.
en-us: When SortOrder is set to Custom, this lua function is used to determine the ordering of elements. Function should take two arguments (each will be an Instance child to compare), and return true if a comes before b, otherwise return false. In other words, use this function the same way you would use a table.sort function. The sorting should be deterministic, otherwise sort will fail and fall back to name order.
zh-cn: 当 SortOrder 被设为 Custom 时，此 lua 函数可用于决定元素的顺序。函数应该有两个参数 (两者均为 Instance 子类以便进行比较)，若 a 在 b 前则返回 true，否则返回 false。换句话说，此函数的使用方式与使用 table.sort 函数相同。排序应当是具有确定性的，否则排序将会失败并恢复按名称排序。

Source: Forces a relayout of all elements. Useful when sort is set to Custom.
en-us: Forces a relayout of all elements. Useful when sort is set to Custom.
zh-cn: 强制对所有元素进行重新布局。排序被设为 Custom 时很有用。

Source: Determines how we decide which element to place next. Can be Name or Custom. If using Custom, make sure SetCustomSortFunction was called with an appropriate sort function.
en-us: Determines how we decide which element to place next. Can be Name or Custom. If using Custom, make sure SetCustomSortFunction was called with an appropriate sort function.
zh-cn: 决定我们将如何决定接下来该放置哪个元素。值可以是 Name 或 Custom。如果使用 Custom，请确保使用适当的排序函数调用 SetCustomSortFunction。

Source: Determines which direction to fill the grid. Can be Horizontal or Vertical.
en-us: Determines which direction to fill the grid. Can be Horizontal or Vertical.
zh-cn: 决定填充网格的方向。可以是 Horizontal 或 Vertical。

Source: Determines how grid is placed within it's parent's container in the x direction. Can be Left, Center, or Right.
en-us: Determines how grid is placed within it's parent's container in the x direction. Can be Left, Center, or Right.
zh-cn: 决定网格在其父容器内 x 方向上的放置方式。值可以是 Left、Center 或 Right。

Source: Determines how grid is placed within it's parent's container in the y direction. Can be Top, Center, or Bottom.
en-us: Determines how grid is placed within it's parent's container in the y direction. Can be Top, Center, or Bottom.
zh-cn: 决定网格在其父容器内 y 方向上的放置方式。值可以是 Left、Center 或 Right。

Source: Sets the position of UI elements in a list. You can use a UIListLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIListLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
en-us: Sets the position of UI elements in a list. You can use a UIListLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIListLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
zh-cn: 设置一个列表中的 UI 元素的位置。可以通过将 UIListLayout 设为 GuiObject 的父类来使用它。随后 UIListLayout 会将其自身应用于所有 GuiObject 的同级类。

Source: Determines the amount of free space between each element. Can be set either using scale (Percentage of parent's size in the current direction) or offset (a static spacing value, similar to pixel size).
en-us: Determines the amount of free space between each element. Can be set either using scale (Percentage of parent's size in the current direction) or offset (a static spacing value, similar to pixel size).
zh-cn: 决定每个元素之间的可用空间量。可以使用比例 (父类在当前方向上的大小百分比) 或偏移 (一个静态间距值，类似于像素大小) 进行设置。

Source: Sets the position of UI elements inline. You can use a UIInlineLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIListLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
en-us: Sets the position of UI elements inline. You can use a UIInlineLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIListLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
zh-cn: 设置轴线上的 UI 元素的位置。可以通过将 UIListLayout 设为 GuiObject 的父类来使用它。随后 UIListLayout 会将其自身应用于所有 GuiObject 的同级类。

Source: Sets the position of UI elements in a 2D grid (this can be modified to 1D grid for list layout). This will also set the elements to a particular size, although this can be overridden with particular constraints on elements. You can use a UIGridLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIGridLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
en-us: Sets the position of UI elements in a 2D grid (this can be modified to 1D grid for list layout). This will also set the elements to a particular size, although this can be overridden with particular constraints on elements. You can use a UIGridLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIGridLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
zh-cn: 设置一个 2D 网格 (可以改为 1D 网格以进行列表布局) 中 UI 元素的位置。同时还会将元素设置为特定大小，但可以通过对元素进行特定约束来覆盖此设置。可以通过将 UIGridLayout 设为 GuiObject 的父类来使用它。随后 UIGridLayout 会将其自身应用于所有 GuiObject 的同级类。

Source: Denotes what size each element should be. Can be overridden by elements using constraints on individual elements.
en-us: Denotes what size each element should be. Can be overridden by elements using constraints on individual elements.
zh-cn: 表示每个元素的大小。可以被使用约束的单独元素覆盖。

Source: How much space between elements there should be.
en-us: How much space between elements there should be.
zh-cn: 元素之间应当存在多大的空间。

Source: Determines how many cells over in the FillDirection we go before starting a new row or column. Set to 0 for max cell count.  Will be clamped if this is set higher than the parent container allows room for.
en-us: Determines how many cells over in the FillDirection we go before starting a new row or column. Set to 0 for max cell count.  Will be clamped if this is set higher than the parent container allows room for.
zh-cn: 决定在 FillDirection 方向上开始新行或新列前我们需要经过多少单元格。设为 0 时取最大单元格数。若此值设定得比父容器所允许的空间大，则会被钳制。

Source: Returns the current size of the grid. If more elements are added, this can increase. If elements are removed this can decrease.
en-us: Returns the current size of the grid. If more elements are added, this can increase. If elements are removed this can decrease.
zh-cn: 返回网格的当前大小。若添加了更多元素，此值会增加。若元素被移除，则此值会减少。

Source: Which corner we start laying the elements out from. Can be TopLeft, TopRight, BottomLeft, BottomRight.
en-us: Which corner we start laying the elements out from. Can be TopLeft, TopRight, BottomLeft, BottomRight.
zh-cn: 我们将会从哪个角开始铺设元素。值可以是 TopLeft、TopRight、BottomLeft 或 BottomRight。

Source: Creates a paged viewing window, like the home screen of a mobile device. You can use a UIPageLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIPageLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
en-us: Creates a paged viewing window, like the home screen of a mobile device. You can use a UIPageLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIPageLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.
zh-cn: 创建一个分页查看窗口，类似移动设备的主屏幕。可以通过将 UIPageLayout 设为 GuiObject 的父类来使用它。随后 UIPageLayout 会将其自身应用于所有 GuiObject 的同级类。

Source: The page that is either currently being displayed or is the target of the current animation.
en-us: The page that is either currently being displayed or is the target of the current animation.
zh-cn: 当前正在显示的页面，或作为当前动画目标的页面。

Source: Whether or not the page layout wraps around at the ends.
en-us: Whether or not the page layout wraps around at the ends.
zh-cn: 页面布局是否在结尾处换行。

Source: Determines the amount that pages are separated from each other by. Can be set either using scale (Percentage of parent's size in the current direction) or offset (a static spacing value, similar to pixel size).
en-us: Determines the amount that pages are separated from each other by. Can be set either using scale (Percentage of parent's size in the current direction) or offset (a static spacing value, similar to pixel size).
zh-cn: 决定页面彼此之间的分离量。可以使用比例 (父类在当前方向上的大小百分比) 或偏移 (一个静态间距值，类似于像素大小) 进行设置。

Source: Whether or not to animate transitions between pages.
en-us: Whether or not to animate transitions between pages.
zh-cn: 页面之间是否使用动画过渡。

Source: The easing style to use when performing an animation.
en-us: The easing style to use when performing an animation.
zh-cn: 执行动画时使用的缓动风格。

Source: The easing direction to use when performing an animation.
en-us: The easing direction to use when performing an animation.
zh-cn: 执行动画时使用的缓动方向。

Source: The length of the animation.
en-us: The length of the animation.
zh-cn: 动画的长度。

Source: Sets CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.
en-us: Sets CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.
zh-cn: 将当前页面的下一页设为 CurrentPage 并执行动画至该页面，如果没有下一页则不执行任何操作。

Source: Sets CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.
en-us: Sets CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.
zh-cn: 将当前页面的下一页设为 CurrentPage 并执行动画至该页面，如果没有下一页则不执行任何操作。

Source: If the instance is in the layout, then it sets CurrentPage to it and animtes to it. If circular layout is set, it will take the shortest path.
en-us: If the instance is in the layout, then it sets CurrentPage to it and animtes to it. If circular layout is set, it will take the shortest path.
zh-cn: 如果实例位于布局中，则将其设为 CurrentPage 并执行动画至其位置。如果设置了环形布局，则会采用最短路径。

Source: If the index is >= 0 and less than the size of the layout, acts like JumpTo. If it's out of bounds and circular is set, it will animate the full distance between the in-bounds index of CurrentPage and the new index.
en-us: If the index is >= 0 and less than the size of the layout, acts like JumpTo. If it's out of bounds and circular is set, it will animate the full distance between the in-bounds index of CurrentPage and the new index.
zh-cn: 如果索引大于等于 0 且小于该布局的大小，表现为 JumpTo。如果超出边界且设置了环形布局，则执行 CurrentPage 的入口索引至新索引之间的全长动画。

Source: Fires when a page comes into view, and is going to be rendered.
en-us: Fires when a page comes into view, and is going to be rendered.
zh-cn: 当页面进入视图时触发，页面会进行渲染。

Source: Fires when a page leaves view, and will not be rendered.
en-us: Fires when a page leaves view, and will not be rendered.
zh-cn: 当页面离开视图时触发，页面不会进行渲染。

Source: Fires when an animation to CurrentPage is completed without being cancelled, and the view stops scrolling.
en-us: Fires when an animation to CurrentPage is completed without being cancelled, and the view stops scrolling.
zh-cn: 当动画执行至 CurrentPage 完成且未被取消时触发，视图停止滚动。

Source: Provides a layout of rows and columns that are sized based on the cells in them.
en-us: Provides a layout of rows and columns that are sized based on the cells in them.
zh-cn: 提供一个拥有行与列的布局，行与列的大小基于其中的单元格。

Source: The amount of padding to insert in between the cells of the table.
en-us: The amount of padding to insert in between the cells of the table.
zh-cn: 表格的单元格之间插入的填充量。

Source: Whether the table should expand to fill the available space of its container, row-wise.
en-us: Whether the table should expand to fill the available space of its container, row-wise.
zh-cn: 是否应扩展表格行以填充其容器的可用空间。

Source: Whether the table should expand to fill the available space of its container, column-wise.
en-us: Whether the table should expand to fill the available space of its container, column-wise.
zh-cn: 是否应扩展表格列以填充其容器的可用空间。

Source: Whether the direct siblings are considered the rows or the columns. The children of the direct siblings are the columns or rows, respectively.
en-us: Whether the direct siblings are considered the rows or the columns. The children of the direct siblings are the columns or rows, respectively.
zh-cn: 直接同级类应被视为行还是列。直接同级类的子类分别为列或行。

Source: Ensures a GuiObject does not become smaller or larger than the min and max size. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.
en-us: Ensures a GuiObject does not become smaller or larger than the min and max size. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.
zh-cn: 确保 GuiObject 不会小于最小尺寸或大于最大尺寸。若拥有约束的元素受布局所控制，该约束优先决定元素的大小而非位置。可以将 Constraint 设置为想约束的元素的父类来使用它。

Source: The smallest size the GuiObject is allowed to be.
en-us: The smallest size the GuiObject is allowed to be.
zh-cn: GuiObject 允许的最小尺寸。

Source: The biggest size the GuiObject is allowed to be.
en-us: The biggest size the GuiObject is allowed to be.
zh-cn: GuiObject 允许的最大尺寸。

Source: Ensures a GuiObject with text does not allow the font size to become larger or smaller than min and max text sizes. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.
en-us: Ensures a GuiObject with text does not allow the font size to become larger or smaller than min and max text sizes. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.
zh-cn: 确保带有文本的 GuiObject 不会允许其字体大小大于最大文本尺寸或小于最小文本尺寸。若拥有约束的元素受布局所控制，该约束优先决定元素的大小而非位置。可以将 Constraint 设置为想约束的元素的父类来使用它。

Source: The smallest size the font is allowed to be.
en-us: The smallest size the font is allowed to be.
zh-cn: 字体允许的最小尺寸。

Source: The biggest size the font is allowed to be.
en-us: The biggest size the font is allowed to be.
zh-cn: 字体允许的最大尺寸。

Source: Ensures a GuiObject will always have a particular aspect ratio. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.
en-us: Ensures a GuiObject will always have a particular aspect ratio. If an element with a constraint is under the control of a layout, the constraint takes precedence in determining the element’s size, but not position. You can use a Constraint by parenting it to the element you wish to constrain.
zh-cn: 确保 GuiObject 始终具有特定的宽高比。若拥有约束的元素受布局所控制，该约束优先决定元素的大小而非位置。可以将 Constraint 设置为想约束的元素的父类来使用它。

Source: The aspect ratio to maintain. This is the width/height. Only positive numbers allowed.
en-us: The aspect ratio to maintain. This is the width/height. Only positive numbers allowed.
zh-cn: 要维持的宽高比。比例为宽/高。只允许正数值。

Source: Describes how the aspect ratio will determine its size. Options are FitWithinMaxSize, ScaleWithParentSize. FitWithinMaxSize will make the element the maximum size it can be within the current possible AbsoluteSize of the element while maintaining the AspectRatio. ScaleWithParentSize will make the element the closest to the parent element’s maximum size while maintaining aspect ratio.
en-us: Describes how the aspect ratio will determine its size. Options are FitWithinMaxSize, ScaleWithParentSize. FitWithinMaxSize will make the element the maximum size it can be within the current possible AbsoluteSize of the element while maintaining the AspectRatio. ScaleWithParentSize will make the element the closest to the parent element’s maximum size while maintaining aspect ratio.
zh-cn: 描述宽高比如何确定其大小。选项包括 FitWithinMaxSize 和 ScaleWithParentSize。FitWithinMaxSize 会在维持 AspectRatio 的同时将元素缩放至其当前可能的 AbsoluteSize 以内的的最大尺寸。ScaleWithParentSize 则会在维持宽高比的同时将元素缩放至最接近其父元素的最大尺寸的大小。

Source: Describes which axis to use when determining the new size of the element, while keeping respect to the aspect ratio.
en-us: Describes which axis to use when determining the new size of the element, while keeping respect to the aspect ratio.
zh-cn: 描述在保持宽高比的同时应使用哪条轴线来决定元素的新尺寸。

Source: Uniformly scales a GUI object and all its children.
en-us: Uniformly scales a GUI object and all its children.
zh-cn: 统一缩放 GUI 对象及其所有子类。

Source: The scale factor to apply.
en-us: The scale factor to apply.
zh-cn: 需应用的缩放比例。

Source: The padding to apply on the left side relative to the parent's normal size.
en-us: The padding to apply on the left side relative to the parent's normal size.
zh-cn: 相对于父类的正常大小，在左侧应用的填充量。

Source: The padding to apply on the right side relative to the parent's normal size.
en-us: The padding to apply on the right side relative to the parent's normal size.
zh-cn: 相对于父类的正常大小，在右侧应用的填充量。

Source: The padding to apply on the top side relative to the parent's normal size.
en-us: The padding to apply on the top side relative to the parent's normal size.
zh-cn: 相对于父类的正常大小，在上方应用的填充量。

Source: The padding to apply on the bottom side relative to the parent's normal size.
en-us: The padding to apply on the bottom side relative to the parent's normal size.
zh-cn: 相对于父类的正常大小，在下方应用的填充量。

Source: The current state of how the tween is animating. Possible values are Begin, Playing, Paused, Completed and Cancelled. This property is modified by using functions such as Tween:Play(), Tween:Pause(), and Tween:Cancel(). Read-only.
en-us: The current state of how the tween is animating. Possible values are Begin, Playing, Paused, Completed and Cancelled. This property is modified by using functions such as Tween:Play(), Tween:Pause(), and Tween:Cancel(). Read-only.
zh-cn: 补间动画的当前状态。可能的值包括 Begin、Playing、Paused、Completed 和 Cancelled。可使用诸如 Tween:Play()、Tween:Pause() 和 Tween:Cancel() 等之类的函数来修改此属性。只读。

Source: Starts or resumes (if Tween.PlaybackState is Paused) the tween animation. If current PlaybackState is Cancelled, this property will reset the tween to the beginning properties and play the animations from the beginning.
en-us: Starts or resumes (if Tween.PlaybackState is Paused) the tween animation. If current PlaybackState is Cancelled, this property will reset the tween to the beginning properties and play the animations from the beginning.
zh-cn: 开始或恢复 (若 Tween.PlaybackState 为 Paused) 执行补间动画。若当前 PlaybackState 为 Cancelled，此属性会重置补间至初始属性并从头开始执行动画。

Source: Temporarily stops the tween animation. Animation can be resumed by calling Play().
en-us: Temporarily stops the tween animation. Animation can be resumed by calling Play().
zh-cn: 暂停执行补间动画。可以调用 Play() 恢复执行动画。

Source: Stops the tween animation. Animation can be restarted by calling Play(). Animation will start from the beginning values.
en-us: Stops the tween animation. Animation can be restarted by calling Play(). Animation will start from the beginning values.
zh-cn: 停止执行补间动画。可以调用 Play() 重新开始执行动画。动画会从初始值开始。

Source: Fires when the tween either reaches PlaybackState Completed or Cancelled. PlaybackState of one of these types is passed as the first arg to the function listening to this event.
en-us: Fires when the tween either reaches PlaybackState Completed or Cancelled. PlaybackState of one of these types is passed as the first arg to the function listening to this event.
zh-cn: 当补间动画的 PlaybackState 到达 Completed 或 Cancelled 时触发。这些类型之一的 PlaybackState 将作为第一个参数传给监听此事件的函数。

Source: An object linked to an instance that animates properties on the instance over a specified period of time. Useful for easily moving UI objects around, rotating objects, etc. without having to write a lot of code. To create a new tween, please use TweenService:Create.
en-us: An object linked to an instance that animates properties on the instance over a specified period of time. Useful for easily moving UI objects around, rotating objects, etc. without having to write a lot of code. To create a new tween, please use TweenService:Create.
zh-cn: 一个链接至实例的对象，可以在指定的时间段内为该实例设置动画属性。可用于便利地移动 UI 对象、旋转物体等，无需编写复杂的代码。若想创建一个新补间动画，请使用 TweenService:Create。

Source: The object this tween is operating on. Read-only.
en-us: The object this tween is operating on. Read-only.
zh-cn: 此补间动画操作的对象。只读。

Source: Specifies how the tween animates. Read-only.
en-us: Specifies how the tween animates. Read-only.
zh-cn: 指定补间动画的执行方式。只读。

Source: Service responsible for creating tweens on instances.
en-us: Service responsible for creating tweens on instances.
zh-cn: 负责在实例上创建补间动画的服务。

Source: Creates a Tween object bound to a particular Instance. The first arg is the Instance to tween. The second arg is a TweenInfo struct, which specifies how a tween should behave. The third arg is a table, which should specify the properties to tween as keys, with the end value specified as values to the keys.
en-us: Creates a Tween object bound to a particular Instance. The first arg is the Instance to tween. The second arg is a TweenInfo struct, which specifies how a tween should behave. The third arg is a table, which should specify the properties to tween as keys, with the end value specified as values to the keys.
zh-cn: 创建一个绑定至特定实例的 Tween 对象。第一个参数是用于创建补间动画的 Instance。第二个参数是 Tweeninfo 结构，用于指定补间动画的行为模式。第三个参数是一个表，应为补间动画指定键属性，并将终值指定为键值。

Source: Transforms a linear alpha to a given EasingStyle and EasingDirection.
en-us: Transforms a linear alpha to a given EasingStyle and EasingDirection.
zh-cn: 将线性 alpha 转换为指定的 EasingStyle 和 EasingDirection。

Source: Will stop/begin certain core gui elements being rendered. See CoreGuiType for core guis that can be modified.
en-us: Will stop/begin certain core gui elements being rendered. See CoreGuiType for core guis that can be modified.
zh-cn: 会停止/开始渲染某些核心 GUI 元素。请参阅 CoreGuiType 以获取可修改的核心 GUI。

Source: Returns a boolean describing whether a CoreGuiType is currently being rendered.
en-us: Returns a boolean describing whether a CoreGuiType is currently being rendered.
zh-cn: 返回描述当前是否正在渲染 CoreGuiType 的布尔值。

Source: The GuiService is a special service, which currently allows developers to control what GuiObject is currently being selected by the Gamepad Gui navigator, and allows clients to check if Roblox's main menu is currently open. This service has a lot of hidden members, which are mainly used internally by Roblox's CoreScripts.
en-us: The GuiService is a special service, which currently allows developers to control what GuiObject is currently being selected by the Gamepad Gui navigator, and allows clients to check if Roblox's main menu is currently open. This service has a lot of hidden members, which are mainly used internally by Roblox's CoreScripts.
zh-cn: GuiServie 是一种特殊服务，目前它可以允许开发者控制 Gamepad Gui 导航器当前选择的 GuiObject，以及允许客户端检查 Roblox 的主菜单当前是否打开。此服务有许多隐藏成员，主要供 Roblox 的 CoreScript 内部使用。

Source: Returns a Tuple containing two Vector2 values representing the offset of user GUIs in pixels from the top right corner of the screen and the bottom right corner of the screen respectively.
en-us: Returns a Tuple containing two Vector2 values representing the offset of user GUIs in pixels from the top right corner of the screen and the bottom right corner of the screen respectively.
zh-cn: 返回一个包含两个 Vector2 值的 Tuple 容器，这两个值分别代表屏幕右上角和右下角的用户 GUI 偏移量 (以像素为单位)。

Source: A service used to bind input to various lua functions.
en-us: A service used to bind input to various lua functions.
zh-cn: 用于将输入绑定至各种 lua 函数的服务。

Source: Binds 'functionToBind' to fire when any 'inputTypes' happen. InputTypes can be variable in number and type. Types can be Enum.KeyCode, single character strings corresponding to keys, or Enum.UserInputType. 'actionName' is a key used by many other ContextActionService functions to query state. 'createTouchButton' if true will create a button on screen on touch devices.  This button will fire 'functionToBind' with three arguments: first argument is the actionName, second argument is the UserInputState of the input, and the third is the InputObject that fired this function. If 'functionToBind' yields or returns nil or Enum.ContextActionResult.Sink, the input will be sunk. If it returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Pass, the next bound action in the stack will be invoked.
en-us: Binds 'functionToBind' to fire when any 'inputTypes' happen. InputTypes can be variable in number and type. Types can be Enum.KeyCode, single character strings corresponding to keys, or Enum.UserInputType. 'actionName' is a key used by many other ContextActionService functions to query state. 'createTouchButton' if true will create a button on screen on touch devices.  This button will fire 'functionToBind' with three arguments: first argument is the actionName, second argument is the UserInputState of the input, and the third is the InputObject that fired this function. If 'functionToBind' yields or returns nil or Enum.ContextActionResult.Sink, the input will be sunk. If it returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Pass, the next bound action in the stack will be invoked.
zh-cn: 将 'functionToBind' 绑定至当任意 'inputTypes' 发生时触发。InputType 可以包括多种数量和类型。Type 的值可以是 Enum.KeyCode、对应按键的单一字符，或 Enum.UserInputType。'actionName' 是许多其他 ContextActionService 函数用于查询状态的键。 'createTouchButton' 若为 true，则会在触屏设备的屏幕上创建一个按钮。此按钮会触发 'functionToBind' 并提供三个参数：第一个参数为 actionName，第二个参数为输入的 UserInputState，第三个参数为触发此函数的 InputObject。若 'functionToBind' 暂停或返回空值或 Enum.ContextActionResult.Sink，输入会被汇聚。若返回 Enum.ContextActionResult.Pass，则调用堆栈中的下一个操作操作。

Source: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'title' is set as the title of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether title will be set when button is manipulated.
en-us: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'title' is set as the title of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether title will be set when button is manipulated.
zh-cn: 若 'actionName' 键包含绑定操作，'title' 将被设为触碰按钮的标题。若未创建触碰按钮，则不执行任何操作。无法保证在操作按钮时是否会设置标题。

Source: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'description' is set as the description of the bound action. This description will appear for users in a listing of current actions availables.
en-us: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'description' is set as the description of the bound action. This description will appear for users in a listing of current actions availables.
zh-cn: 若 'actionName' 键包含绑定操作，'description' 将被设为绑定操作的描述。此描述会出现在用户当前可用操作的列表中。

Source: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'image' is set as the image of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether image will be set when button is manipulated.
en-us: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'image' is set as the image of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether image will be set when button is manipulated.
zh-cn: 若 'actionName' 键包含绑定操作，'image' 将被设为触碰按钮的图像。若未创建触碰按钮，则不执行任何操作。无法保证在操作按钮时是否会设置图像。

Source: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'position' is set as the position of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether position will be set when button is manipulated.
en-us: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'position' is set as the position of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether position will be set when button is manipulated.
zh-cn: 若 'actionName' 键包含绑定操作，'position' 将被设为触碰按钮的位置。若未创建触碰按钮，则不执行任何操作。无法保证在操作按钮时是否会设置位置。

Source: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, removes function from being called by all input that it was bound by (if function was also bound by a different action name as well, those bound input are still active). Will also remove any touch button created (if button was manipulated manually there is no guarantee it will be cleaned up).
