Source: A type of DataStore where values must be positive integers. This makes OrderedDataStore suitable for leaderboard related scripting where you are required to order large amounts of data efficiently.
en-us: A type of DataStore where values must be positive integers. This makes OrderedDataStore suitable for leaderboard related scripting where you are required to order large amounts of data efficiently.
zh-cn: 一种 DataStore 类型，其值必须为正整数。这使得 OrderedDataStore 适用于需要给大量数据高效排序的排行榜相关脚本。

Source: Returns a DataStorePages object. The length of each page is determined by pageSize, and the order is determined by isAscending. minValue and maxValue are optional parameters which will filter the result.
en-us: Returns a DataStorePages object. The length of each page is determined by pageSize, and the order is determined by isAscending. minValue and maxValue are optional parameters which will filter the result.
zh-cn: 返回一个 DataStorePages 对象。每页的长度由 pageSize 决定，顺序由 isAscending 决定。minValue 和 maxValue 为用于过滤结果的可选参数。

Source: Where the Camera's focus is.  Any rotation of the camera will be about this subject.
en-us: Where the Camera's focus is.  Any rotation of the camera will be about this subject.
zh-cn: 镜头的焦点所在位置。对镜头的一切旋转都将围绕此对象进行。

Source: Defines how the camera will behave. More info
en-us: Defines how the camera will behave. More info
zh-cn: 定义镜头的行为方式。更多信息

Source: The current position and rotation of the Camera.  For most CameraTypes, the rotation is set such that the CoordinateFrame lookVector is pointing at the Focus.
en-us: The current position and rotation of the Camera.  For most CameraTypes, the rotation is set such that the CoordinateFrame lookVector is pointing at the Focus.
zh-cn: 镜头的当前位置和旋转值。对于大多数 CameraType 而言，旋转值为 CoordinateFrame 的 lookVector 指向 Focus。

Source: The current position and rotation of the Camera.  For most CameraTypes, the rotation is set such that the CoordinateFrame lookVector is pointing at the Focus.
en-us: The current position and rotation of the Camera.  For most CameraTypes, the rotation is set such that the CoordinateFrame lookVector is pointing at the Focus.
zh-cn: 镜头的当前位置和旋转值。对于大多数 CameraType 而言，旋转值为 CoordinateFrame 的 lookVector 指向 Focus。

Source: The current angle, or width, of what the camera can see.  Current acceptable values are from 20 degrees to 80.
en-us: The current angle, or width, of what the camera can see.  Current acceptable values are from 20 degrees to 80.
zh-cn: 镜头当前可见的角度或宽度。当前可接受的值为 20 至 80 度。

Source: The current CoordinateFrame that the camera is looking at.  Note: it is not always guaranteed that the camera is always looking here.
en-us: The current CoordinateFrame that the camera is looking at.  Note: it is not always guaranteed that the camera is always looking here.
zh-cn: 镜头当前朝向的 CoordinateFrame 。注: 不能保证镜头总是看向这里。

Source: Holds the x,y screen resolution of the viewport the camera is presenting (note: this can differ from the AbsoluteSize property of a full screen gui).
en-us: Holds the x,y screen resolution of the viewport the camera is presenting (note: this can differ from the AbsoluteSize property of a full screen gui).
zh-cn: 储存镜头所呈现的观察窗的屏幕分辨率 x,y 值 (注: 此数值可能与全屏图形界面的 AbsoluteSize 属性有所不同)。

Source: The negative z-offset of the view frustum's near clipping plane.
en-us: The negative z-offset of the view frustum's near clipping plane.
zh-cn: 视椎体近剪切平面的负 z 轴偏移

Source: Returns the camera's current roll. Roll is defined in radians, and is stored as the delta from the camera's y axis default normal vector.
en-us: Returns the camera's current roll. Roll is defined in radians, and is stored as the delta from the camera's y axis default normal vector.
zh-cn: 返回镜头的当前翻滚值。翻滚值以弧度为单位，并储存为镜头 y 轴默认法矢量的 delta 值。

Source: Takes a 3D position in the world and projects it onto x,y coordinates of screen space. Returns two values, first is a Vector3 that has x,y position and z position which is distance from camera (negative if behind camera, positive if in front). Second return value is a boolean indicating if the first argument is an on-screen coordinate.
en-us: Takes a 3D position in the world and projects it onto x,y coordinates of screen space. Returns two values, first is a Vector3 that has x,y position and z position which is distance from camera (negative if behind camera, positive if in front). Second return value is a boolean indicating if the first argument is an on-screen coordinate.
zh-cn: 取世界中的一个 3D 位置并将其映射至屏幕空间的 x,y 坐标。返回两个值，第一个是包含 x,y 位置和定义与镜头距离的 z 位置 (负数为在镜头后，正数为在镜头前) 的 Vector3。第二个返回值是判断第一个参数是否为屏幕上的坐标的布尔值。

Source: Takes a 2D screen position and produces a Ray object to be used for 3D raycasting. Input is x,y screen coordinates, and a (optional, defaults to 0) z position which sets how far in the camera look vector to start the ray origin.
en-us: Takes a 2D screen position and produces a Ray object to be used for 3D raycasting. Input is x,y screen coordinates, and a (optional, defaults to 0) z position which sets how far in the camera look vector to start the ray origin.
zh-cn: 取屏幕上的一个 2D 位置并生成一个用于 3D 光线投射的 Ray 对象。输入为 x,y 屏幕坐标，(可选，默认为0) 的 z 位置设置镜头看向光线原点的矢量距离。

Source: Same as ScreenPointToRay, except no GUI offsets are taken into account. Useful for things like casting a ray from the middle of the Camera.ViewportSize
en-us: Same as ScreenPointToRay, except no GUI offsets are taken into account. Useful for things like casting a ray from the middle of the Camera.ViewportSize
zh-cn: 同 ScreenPointToRay，但不计入 GUI 偏移。适用于从 Camera.ViewportSize 中央投射光线等。

Source: Same as WorldToScreenPoint, except no GUI offsets are taken into account.
en-us: Same as WorldToScreenPoint, except no GUI offsets are taken into account.
zh-cn: 同 WorldToScreenPoint，但不计入 GUI 偏移。

Source: Sets the camera's current roll. Roll is defined in radians, and is stored as the delta from the camera's y axis default normal vector.
en-us: Sets the camera's current roll. Roll is defined in radians, and is stored as the delta from the camera's y axis default normal vector.
zh-cn: 设置镜头的当前翻滚值。翻滚值以弧度为单位，并储存为镜头 y 轴默认法矢量的 delta 值。

Source: Set to true, when a player joins a game, they get a character automatically, as well as when they die.  When set to false, characters do not auto load and will only load in using Player:LoadCharacter().
en-us: Set to true, when a player joins a game, they get a character automatically, as well as when they die.  When set to false, characters do not auto load and will only load in using Player:LoadCharacter().
zh-cn: 若设为真，玩家加入游戏和死亡时会自动获得一个角色。若设为假，角色不会自动加载，只有在使用 Player:LoadCharacter() 时才会加载。

Source: Use GetPlayers() instead
en-us: Use GetPlayers() instead
zh-cn: 请改用 GetPlayers()

Source: A container whose contents are replicated to all clients and the server.
en-us: A container whose contents are replicated to all clients and the server.
zh-cn: 一个容器，其内容被复制到所有客户端和服务器。

Source: A container whose contents are replicated to all clients (but not back to the server) first before anything else. Useful for creating loading guis, tutorials, etc.
en-us: A container whose contents are replicated to all clients (but not back to the server) first before anything else. Useful for creating loading guis, tutorials, etc.
zh-cn: 一个容器，其内容在进行其他一切操作前先被复制到所有客户端 (但不会返回到服务器)。适用于创建载入图形界面、教程等。

Source: Removes the default Roblox loading screen from view. Call this when you are ready to either show your own loading gui, or when the game is ready to play.
en-us: Removes the default Roblox loading screen from view. Call this when you are ready to either show your own loading gui, or when the game is ready to play.
zh-cn: 从视图中移除默认 Roblox 载入页面。当你准备好显示自己的载入界面或当游戏已准备就绪时调用。

Source: A container whose contents are only on the server.
en-us: A container whose contents are only on the server.
zh-cn: 一个容器，其内容仅存在于服务器上。

Source: A container whose contents should be scripts. Scripts that are added to the container are run on the server.
en-us: A container whose contents should be scripts. Scripts that are added to the container are run on the server.
zh-cn: 一个容器，其内容应为脚本。添加至该容器的脚本将在服务器上运行。

Source: A service for interfacing with the current studio state from Lua.
en-us: A service for interfacing with the current studio state from Lua.
zh-cn: 用于与 Lua 的当前 Studio 状态进行交互的服务。

Source: Responsible for all lighting aspects of the world (affects how things are rendered).
en-us: Responsible for all lighting aspects of the world (affects how things are rendered).
zh-cn: 负责游戏世界中的所有照明外观 (影响物体的渲染方式)。

Source: The number of minutes that the current time is past midnight.  If currently at midnight, returns 0.  Will return decimal values if not at an exact minute.
en-us: The number of minutes that the current time is past midnight.  If currently at midnight, returns 0.  Will return decimal values if not at an exact minute.
zh-cn: 从午夜开始到当前时间的分钟数。若当前时间为午夜，则返回 0。若未处于准确分钟，将返回小数值。

Source: Returns the lookVector (Vector3) of the moon. If this lookVector was used in a CFrame, the Part would face the moon.
en-us: Returns the lookVector (Vector3) of the moon. If this lookVector was used in a CFrame, the Part would face the moon.
zh-cn: 返回月球的 lookVector (Vector3)。若此 lookVector 被用于 CFrame 中，Part 将面向月球。

Source: Currently always returns 0.75. MoonPhase cannot be edited.
en-us: Currently always returns 0.75. MoonPhase cannot be edited.
zh-cn: 目前总是返回 0.75。MoonPhase 无法被编辑。

Source: Returns the lookVector (Vector3) of the sun. If this lookVector was used in a CFrame, the Part would face the sun.
en-us: Returns the lookVector (Vector3) of the sun. If this lookVector was used in a CFrame, the Part would face the sun.
zh-cn: 返回太阳的 lookVector (Vector3)。若此 lookVector 被用于 CFrame 中，Part 将面向太阳。

Source: Sets the time to be a certain number of minutes after midnight.  This works with integer and decimal values.
en-us: Sets the time to be a certain number of minutes after midnight.  This works with integer and decimal values.
zh-cn: 设置时间为从午夜开始经过的一定分钟数。可为整数或小数值。

Source: The hue of the global lighting.  Changing this changes the color tint of all objects in the Workspace.
en-us: The hue of the global lighting.  Changing this changes the color tint of all objects in the Workspace.
zh-cn: 全局照明的色调。修改此值会改变工作区中所有对象的颜色色调。

Source: How much global light each Part in the Workspace receives. Standard range is 0 to 2 (0 being little light), but can be increased all the way to 10 (colors start to be appear very different at this value).
en-us: How much global light each Part in the Workspace receives. Standard range is 0 to 2 (0 being little light), but can be increased all the way to 10 (colors start to be appear very different at this value).
zh-cn: 工作区中的每个 Part 能接收到多少全局光照。标准范围为 0 至 2 (0 为极少光照)，但也可以增加至 10 (从此数值开始色彩会显得极为不同)。

Source: Exposure compensation amount. Applies a bias to the exposure level prior to the tonemap step. +1 indicates twice as much exposure and -1 means half as much exposure.
en-us: Exposure compensation amount. Applies a bias to the exposure level prior to the tonemap step. +1 indicates twice as much exposure and -1 means half as much exposure.
zh-cn: 曝光补偿值。在色调映射步骤前对曝光级别应用偏差值。+1 代表曝光量加倍，-1 代表曝光量减半。

Source: This property controls how blurry the shadows are.
en-us: This property controls how blurry the shadows are.
zh-cn: 此属性控制阴影的模糊程度。

Source: The hue of global lighting on the bottom surfaces of an object.
en-us: The hue of global lighting on the bottom surfaces of an object.
zh-cn: 物体底表面的全局照明色调。

Source: The hue of global lighting on the top surfaces of an object.
en-us: The hue of global lighting on the top surfaces of an object.
zh-cn: 物体顶表面的全局照明色调。

Source: A Color3 value that changes the hue of distance fog.
en-us: A Color3 value that changes the hue of distance fog.
zh-cn: 用于改变远方迷雾色调的 Color3 值。

Source: The distance at which fog completely blocks your vision. This distance is relative to the camera position. Units are in studs
en-us: The distance at which fog completely blocks your vision. This distance is relative to the camera position. Units are in studs
zh-cn: 迷雾能完全阻隔你的视线的距离。此距离与镜头位置有关。单位为格

Source: The distance at which the fog gradient begins. This distance is relative to the camera position. Units are in studs.
en-us: The distance at which the fog gradient begins. This distance is relative to the camera position. Units are in studs.
zh-cn: 迷雾渐变开始的距离。此距离与镜头位置有关。单位为格。

Source: The latitude position the level is placed at. This affects sun position. More info
en-us: The latitude position the level is placed at. This affects sun position. More info
zh-cn: 关卡所在的纬度位置。此设定会影响太阳的位置。更多信息

Source: Flag enabling shadows from sun and moon in the place
en-us: Flag enabling shadows from sun and moon in the place
zh-cn: 代表启用场景中太阳和月亮所造成的阴影

Source: Effective ambient value for outdoors, effectively shadow color outdoors (requires GlobalShadows enabled)
en-us: Effective ambient value for outdoors, effectively shadow color outdoors (requires GlobalShadows enabled)
zh-cn: 户外有效环境值，户外有效阴影值 (需启用 GlobalShadows)

Source: Flag enabling or disabling outlines on parts and terrain
en-us: Flag enabling or disabling outlines on parts and terrain
zh-cn: 代表显示或隐藏部件和地形的轮廓线

Source: Color the shadows appear as. Shadows are drawn mostly for characters, but depending on the lighting will also show for Parts in the Workspace.  Rendering settings can also affect if shadows are drawn.
en-us: Color the shadows appear as. Shadows are drawn mostly for characters, but depending on the lighting will also show for Parts in the Workspace.  Rendering settings can also affect if shadows are drawn.
zh-cn: 阴影的显示颜色。大多数情况下只对角色绘制阴影，但根据照明条件，也可能显示工作区中 Part 的阴影。渲染设定也会影响是否绘制阴影。

Source: A string that represent the current time of day. Time is in 24-hour clock format "XX::YY:ZZ", where X is hour, Y is minute, and Z is seconds.
en-us: A string that represent the current time of day. Time is in 24-hour clock format "XX::YY:ZZ", where X is hour, Y is minute, and Z is seconds.
zh-cn: 代表一天中当前时间的字符串。时间使用 24 小时制时钟格式 "XX::YY:ZZ"，其中 X 代表小时，Y 代表分钟，Z 代表秒。

Source: Fired whenever a property of Lighting is changed, or a skybox is added or removed. Skyboxes are of type 'Sky' and should be parented directly to lighting.
en-us: Fired whenever a property of Lighting is changed, or a skybox is added or removed. Skyboxes are of type 'Sky' and should be parented directly to lighting.
zh-cn: 每当 Lighting 的属性变动，或 Skybox 被添加或移除时触发。 Skybox 属于 'Sky' 类型且应为 Lighting 的直接子类。

Source: A service that provides utility in cleaning up objects
en-us: A service that provides utility in cleaning up objects
zh-cn: 提供清理对象实用工具的服务

Source: Adds an Instance into the debris service that will later be destroyed.  Second argument 'lifetime' is optional and specifies how long (in seconds) to wait before destroying the item. If no time is specified then the item added will automatically be destroyed in 10 seconds.
en-us: Adds an Instance into the debris service that will later be destroyed.  Second argument 'lifetime' is optional and specifies how long (in seconds) to wait before destroying the item. If no time is specified then the item added will automatically be destroyed in 10 seconds.
zh-cn: 向稍后将被销毁的碎片服务添加一个 Instance。第二个参数 'lifetime' 为可选项，指定项目被销毁前的等待时间 (以秒为单位)。若不指定时间，则被添加的项目将在 10 秒后被自动销毁。

Source: Deprecated. No replacement
en-us: Deprecated. No replacement
zh-cn: 已过时。无替代

Source: An enum that describes how a Player's camera is allowed to behave. More info.
en-us: An enum that describes how a Player's camera is allowed to behave. More info.
zh-cn: 描述 Player 的镜头的可用行为方式的枚举。更多信息。

Source: Read-only. If true, this Player's persistent data can be loaded, false otherwise. Info on Data Persistence.
en-us: Read-only. If true, this Player's persistent data can be loaded, false otherwise. Info on Data Persistence.
zh-cn: 只读。若值为 true，此 Player 的持久性数据可被载入，值为 false 则相反。关于数据持久性的信息。

Source: Loads in a new character for this player.  This will replace the player's current character, if they have one. This should be used in conjunction with Players.CharacterAutoLoads to control spawning of characters. This function only works from a server-side script (NOT a LocalScript).
en-us: Loads in a new character for this player.  This will replace the player's current character, if they have one. This should be used in conjunction with Players.CharacterAutoLoads to control spawning of characters. This function only works from a server-side script (NOT a LocalScript).
zh-cn: 为此玩家载入一个新角色。若该玩家已有角色，将取代其当前角色。应结合 Players.CharacterAutoLoads 使用，用于控制角色的再生。此函数仅适用于服务器端脚本 (非 LocalScript)。

Source: Use GetPlayerFromCharacter() instead
en-us: Use GetPlayerFromCharacter() instead
zh-cn: 请改用 GetPlayerFromCharacter()

Source: Yields until the persistent data for this Player is ready to be loaded. Info on Data Persistence.
en-us: Yields until the persistent data for this Player is ready to be loaded. Info on Data Persistence.
zh-cn: 暂停直到此 Player 的持久性数据已准备好被载入。关于数据持久性的信息。"

Source: Fired periodically after the user has been AFK for a while.  Currently this event is only fired for the *local* Player.  "time" is the time in seconds that the user has been idle.
en-us: Fired periodically after the user has been AFK for a while.  Currently this event is only fired for the *local* Player.  "time" is the time in seconds that the user has been idle.
zh-cn: 用户进入 AFK (离开) 状态一段时间后定期触发。当前此事件仅针对 *本地* Player 触发。“time”是用户进入离开状态的时间 (以秒为单位)。

Source: Returns parts in the area defined by the Region3, up to specified maxCount or 100, whichever is less
en-us: Returns parts in the area defined by the Region3, up to specified maxCount or 100, whichever is less
zh-cn: 返回由 Region3 指定区域内的部件，最多 maxCount 或 100 个，以较小者为准

Source: Returns parts in the area defined by the Region3, up to specified maxCount or 100, whichever is less
en-us: Returns parts in the area defined by the Region3, up to specified maxCount or 100, whichever is less
zh-cn: 返回由 Region3 指定区域内的部件，最多 maxCount 或 100 个，以较小者为准

Source: Return type is (BasePart, Vector3) if the ray hits.  If it misses it will return (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)
en-us: Return type is (BasePart, Vector3) if the ray hits.  If it misses it will return (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)
zh-cn: 若光线命中，则返回类型 (BasePart, Vector3)。若未命中则返回R (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)

Source: Return type is (BasePart, Vector3) if the ray hits.  If it misses it will return (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)
en-us: Return type is (BasePart, Vector3) if the ray hits.  If it misses it will return (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)
zh-cn: 若光线命中，则返回类型 (BasePart, Vector3)。若未命中则返回R (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)

Source: Boolean used to enable the new physics solver
en-us: Boolean used to enable the new physics solver
zh-cn: 布尔值，用于启用新物理解决器

Source: Sets the height at which falling characters and parts are destroyed. This property is not scriptable and can only be set in Studio
en-us: Sets the height at which falling characters and parts are destroyed. This property is not scriptable and can only be set in Studio
zh-cn: 设置下落的角色和部件会被破坏的高度。此属性不可用于脚本，只能在 Studio 中进行设置

Source: A structural class, not creatable
en-us: A structural class, not creatable
zh-cn: 结构类，不可创建

Source: Color3 of the part.
en-us: Color3 of the part.
zh-cn: 部件的 Color3。

Source: Contains information regarding the Part's position and a matrix that defines the Part's rotation. Can read/write. More info
en-us: Contains information regarding the Part's position and a matrix that defines the Part's rotation. Can read/write. More info
zh-cn: 包含关于 Part 的位置的信息和定义 Part 旋转值的矩阵。可读写。更多信息

Source: Determines whether physical interactions with other Parts are respected.  If true, will collide and react with physics to other Parts.  If false, other parts will pass thru instead of colliding
en-us: Determines whether physical interactions with other Parts are respected.  If true, will collide and react with physics to other Parts.  If false, other parts will pass thru instead of colliding
zh-cn: 决定是否遵守与其他 Part 的物理学互动。若值为 true，将与其他 Part 碰撞和互动。若值为 false，其他部件会穿过而非碰撞

Source: Determines whether or not physics acts upon the Part.  If true, part stays 'Anchored' in space, not moving regardless of any collision/forces acting upon it.  If false, physics works normally on the part.
en-us: Determines whether or not physics acts upon the Part.  If true, part stays 'Anchored' in space, not moving regardless of any collision/forces acting upon it.  If false, physics works normally on the part.
zh-cn: 决定 Part 是否遵守物理学原理。若值为真，部件会被“锚固”在空间中，不会因为对其造成的碰撞和力而移动。若值为 true，部件将遵守一般物理学原理。

Source: If true the part will be massless when welded to another part that is not massless. The part will still have mass like a normal part if it is an assembly root part according to GetRootPart().
en-us: If true the part will be massless when welded to another part that is not massless. The part will still have mass like a normal part if it is an assembly root part according to GetRootPart().
zh-cn: 若值为 true，部件在接合至另一个非无质量的部件时将变为无质量。若部件是一个根据 GetRootPart() 确定的装配根部件，它仍会像一个正常部件一样具有质量。

Source: An integer from -127 to 127. Compares before other all other part properties besides massless for deciding which part is the assembly root part according to GetRootPart().
en-us: An integer from -127 to 127. Compares before other all other part properties besides massless for deciding which part is the assembly root part according to GetRootPart().
zh-cn: -127 到 127 之间的整数。在除无质量外的其他所有部件属性之前进行比较，以确定哪个部件是根据  GetRootPart() 确定的装配根部件。

Source: A float value ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f. Sets how much the Part will rebound against another. a value of 1 is like a superball, and 0 is like a lead block.
en-us: A float value ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f. Sets how much the Part will rebound against another. a value of 1 is like a superball, and 0 is like a lead block.
zh-cn: 0.0f 到 1.0f 之间的浮点值。设置 Part 相互间的反弹系数。值为 1 时相当于橡皮球，值为 0 时相当于铅块。

Source: A float value ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f. Sets how much the Part will be able to slide. a value of 1 is no sliding, and 0 is no friction, so infinite sliding.
en-us: A float value ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f. Sets how much the Part will be able to slide. a value of 1 is no sliding, and 0 is no friction, so infinite sliding.
zh-cn: 0.0f 到 1.0f 之间的浮点值。设置 Part 的滑行能力。值为 1 时无法滑动，值为 0 时无摩擦力，即可以无限滑行。

Source: Determines whether building tools (in-game and studio) can manipulate this Part.  If true, no editing allowed.  If false, editing is allowed.
en-us: Determines whether building tools (in-game and studio) can manipulate this Part.  If true, no editing allowed.  If false, editing is allowed.
zh-cn: 决定建造工具 (游戏内和 Studio 中) 是否可操作此 Part。值为 true 时不允许编辑。值为 false 时允许编辑。

Source: Determines whether this Part casts a shadow.
en-us: Determines whether this Part casts a shadow.
zh-cn: 决定此 Part 是否投射阴影。

Source: Specifies the look and feel the Part should have. Note: this does not define the color the Part is, see BrickColor for that. More info
en-us: Specifies the look and feel the Part should have. Note: this does not define the color the Part is, see BrickColor for that. More info
zh-cn: 指定 Part 应有的外观和感觉。注: 不会定义 Part 的颜色，若需定义该值，请参阅 BrickColor。更多信息

Source: Specifies how shiny the Part is. A value of 1 is completely reflective (chrome), while a value of 0 is no reflectance (concrete wall)
en-us: Specifies how shiny the Part is. A value of 1 is completely reflective (chrome), while a value of 0 is no reflectance (concrete wall)
zh-cn: 指定 Part 的光泽度。值为 1 时完全反射 (铬)，值为 0 时无反射 (混凝土墙)

Source: Sets the value for the smallest change in size allowable by the Resize(NormalId, int) function.
en-us: Sets the value for the smallest change in size allowable by the Resize(NormalId, int) function.
zh-cn: 设置 Resize(NormalId, int) 函数允许改变尺寸的最小改动值。

Source: Sets the value for the faces allowed to be resized by the Resize(NormalId, int) function.
en-us: Sets the value for the faces allowed to be resized by the Resize(NormalId, int) function.
zh-cn: 设置 Resize(NormalId, int) 函数允许改变尺寸的面的值。

Source: Sets how visible an object is. A value of 1 makes the object invisible, while a value of 0 makes the object opaque.
en-us: Sets how visible an object is. A value of 1 makes the object invisible, while a value of 0 makes the object opaque.
zh-cn: 设置物体的可见程度。值为 1 时物体不可见，值为 0 时物体完全不透明。

Source: How fast the Part is traveling in studs/second. This property is NOT recommended to be modified directly, unless there is good reason.  Otherwise, try using a BodyForce to move a Part.
en-us: How fast the Part is traveling in studs/second. This property is NOT recommended to be modified directly, unless there is good reason.  Otherwise, try using a BodyForce to move a Part.
zh-cn: Part 的行进速度，以格/秒为单位。除非理由充分，否则不推荐直接修改此属性。请尝试使用 BodyForce 来移动 Part。

Source: Position relative to parent part, or global space if there is no parent.
en-us: Position relative to parent part, or global space if there is no parent.
zh-cn: 相对父部件的位置，或无父部件时相对全局空间的位置。

Source: Orientation relative to parent part, or global space if there is no parent.
en-us: Orientation relative to parent part, or global space if there is no parent.
zh-cn: 相对父部件的朝向，或无父部件时相对全局空间的朝向。

Source: Rotation around X, Y, and Z axis.  Rotations applied in YXZ order.
en-us: Rotation around X, Y, and Z axis.  Rotations applied in YXZ order.
zh-cn: 围绕 X、Y 和 Z 轴的旋转值。按 YXZ 顺序旋转。

Source: Creates the appropriate SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model). This uses the SurfaceTypes defined on the surfaces of parts to create the appropriate welds. More info
en-us: Creates the appropriate SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model). This uses the SurfaceTypes defined on the surfaces of parts to create the appropriate welds. More info
zh-cn: 使用接触到此 Instance 的所有 Part 创建适当的 SurfaceJoint (包括如 Model 等 Instance 中的内部接头)。利用部件表面定义的 SurfaceType 来创建适当的接合。更多信息

Source: Destroys SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model).
en-us: Destroys SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model).
zh-cn: 销毁接触到此 Instance 的所有部件的 SurfaceJoint（包括 Instance 中的内部接头，如在 Model 中）。

Source: Returns a number that is the mass of this Instance.  Mass of a Part is immutable, and is changed only by the size of the Part.
en-us: Returns a number that is the mass of this Instance.  Mass of a Part is immutable, and is changed only by the size of the Part.
zh-cn: 请改用 GetMass()

Source: Resizes a Part in the direction of the face defined by 'NormalId', by the amount specified by 'deltaAmount'. If the operation will expand the part to intersect another Instance, the part will not resize at all.  Return true if the call is successful, false otherwise.
en-us: Resizes a Part in the direction of the face defined by 'NormalId', by the amount specified by 'deltaAmount'. If the operation will expand the part to intersect another Instance, the part will not resize at all.  Return true if the call is successful, false otherwise.
zh-cn: 根据 'NormalId' 定义的面的方向，根据 'deltaAmount' 指定的数值调整 Part 的大小。若此操作会拓展部件至其与其他 Instance 相交，则部件不会被调整大小。若调用成功返回 true，否则返回 false。

Source: Deprecated. Use Touched instead
en-us: Deprecated. Use Touched instead
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 Touched

Source: Deprecated. Use TouchEnded instead
en-us: Deprecated. Use TouchEnded instead
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 TouchEnded

Source: Fired when the part stops touching another part
en-us: Fired when the part stops touching another part
zh-cn: 当部件停止接触其他部件时触发

Source: A plastic building block - the fundamental component of ROBLOX
en-us: A plastic building block - the fundamental component of ROBLOX
zh-cn: 一块塑料积木— ROBLOX 的基本组件

Source: An extendable building truss
en-us: An extendable building truss
zh-cn: 可扩展的建筑桁架

Source: A Wedge Part
en-us: A Wedge Part
zh-cn: 一个楔形部件

Source: A Prism Part
en-us: A Prism Part
zh-cn: 一个棱形部件

Source: A Pyramid Part
en-us: A Pyramid Part
zh-cn: 一个金字塔部件

Source: A ParallelRamp Part
en-us: A ParallelRamp Part
zh-cn: 一个并行斜坡部件

Source: A RightAngleRamp Part
en-us: A RightAngleRamp Part
zh-cn: 一个右角斜坡部件

Source: A CornerWedge Part
en-us: A CornerWedge Part
zh-cn: 一个转角楔形部件

Source: A container instance that syncs data between a single player and the server.  ScreenGui objects that are placed in this container will be shown to the Player parent only
en-us: A container instance that syncs data between a single player and the server.  ScreenGui objects that are placed in this container will be shown to the Player parent only
zh-cn: 一个容器实例，用于在单个玩家和服务器之间同步数据。放置在此容器中的 ScreenGui 对象只会对 Player 父类显示

Source: Overrides the default selection adornment (used for gamepads). For best results, this should point to a GuiObject.
en-us: Overrides the default selection adornment (used for gamepads). For best results, this should point to a GuiObject.
zh-cn: 覆盖默认选择装饰 (用于游戏手柄)。为了获得最佳效果，应指向一个 GuiObject。

Source: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be exectue only when a Player is the parent.
en-us: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be exectue only when a Player is the parent.
zh-cn: 一个包含 LocalScript 的容器实例。放置在此容器中的 LocalScript 对象只会在作为 Player 的子类时执行。

Source: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be copied to new Players on startup.
en-us: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be copied to new Players on startup.
zh-cn: 一个包含 LocalScript 的容器实例。放置在此容器中的 LocalScript 对象会在启动时复制给新玩家。

Source: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be copied to new characters on startup.
en-us: A container instance that contains LocalScripts.  LocalScript objects that are placed in this container will be copied to new characters on startup.
zh-cn: 一个包含 LocalScript 的容器实例。放置在此容器中的 LocalScript 对象会在启动时复制给新角色。

Source: Deprecated, please use ScreenGui
en-us: Deprecated, please use ScreenGui
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 ScreenGui

Source: The base class of ScreenGui, BillboardGui, and SurfaceGui.
en-us: The base class of ScreenGui, BillboardGui, and SurfaceGui.
zh-cn: ScreenGui、BillboardGui 和 SurfaceGui 的基类。

Source: The core GUI object on which tools are built.  Add Frames/Labels/Buttons to this object to have them rendered as a 2D overlay
en-us: The core GUI object on which tools are built.  Add Frames/Labels/Buttons to this object to have them rendered as a 2D overlay
zh-cn: 打造工具所需的核心 GUI 对象。为对象添加帧/标签/按钮，将它们渲染为 2D 覆盖

Source: Deprecated. Use TestService instead
en-us: Deprecated. Use TestService instead
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 TestService

Source: A GUI that adorns an object in the 3D world.  Add Frames/Labels/Buttons to this object to have them rendered while attached to a 3D object
en-us: A GUI that adorns an object in the 3D world.  Add Frames/Labels/Buttons to this object to have them rendered while attached to a 3D object
zh-cn: 用于装饰 3D 世界中的对象的 GUI。为此对象添加 Frame/Label/Button，以便在附加到 3D 对象时进行渲染

Source: The Object the billboard gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.
en-us: The Object the billboard gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.
zh-cn: 排行榜 GUI 用作渲染的基础 Object。目前只能通过脚本设置此属性，且必须存在于工作区中。只有当指定对象派生自 BasePart 时才会进行渲染。

Source: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.
en-us: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.
zh-cn: 一个表明 GuiObject 在像素空间中的当前位置 (x, y) 的只读 Vector2 值，以 GuiObject 的左上角为准。

Source: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.
en-us: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.
zh-cn: 一个表明 GuiObject 在像素空间中的当前大小 (宽，高) 的只读 Vector2 值。

Source: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.
en-us: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.
zh-cn: 若值为 true，此 GuiObject 可触发鼠标事件并将其传递给下层 GuiObject，若值为否则无上述功能。

Source: If true, billboard gui does not get occluded by 3D objects, but always renders on the screen.
en-us: If true, billboard gui does not get occluded by 3D objects, but always renders on the screen.
zh-cn: 若值为 true，排行榜 GUI 不会被 3D 对象遮挡，而是始终渲染在屏幕上。

Source: If true, billboard gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.
en-us: If true, billboard gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.
zh-cn: 若值为 true，排行榜 GUI 会被渲染，否则将会跳过渲染。

Source: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the extents of the 3d object it is rendering from.
en-us: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the extents of the 3d object it is rendering from.
zh-cn: 一个定义 GUI 与其渲染的 3D 对象范围的相对偏移值的 Vector3 (x,y,z)，以格为单位。

Source: Specifies a Player that the BillboardGui will not render to.
en-us: Specifies a Player that the BillboardGui will not render to.
zh-cn: 指定 BillboardGui 不会渲染的 Player。

Source: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the centroid of the 3d object it is rendering from
en-us: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the centroid of the 3d object it is rendering from
zh-cn: 一个定义 GUI 与其渲染的 3D 对象质心的相对偏移值的 Vector3 (x,y,z)，以格为单位

Source: A Vector2 (x,y) defined in studs that will offset the gui size from it's current size.
en-us: A Vector2 (x,y) defined in studs that will offset the gui size from it's current size.
zh-cn: 一个定义 GUI 与其当前大小的相对偏移值的 Vector2 (x,y)，以格为单位。

Source: A UDim2 value describing the size of the BillboardGui. More information on UDim2 is available here. Relative values are defined as one-to-one with studs.
en-us: A UDim2 value describing the size of the BillboardGui. More information on UDim2 is available here. Relative values are defined as one-to-one with studs.
zh-cn: 一个描述 BillboardGui 大小的 UDim2 值。更多关于 UDim2 的信息请参阅这里。所定义的相关值与格一一对应。

Source: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the billboard gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.
en-us: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the billboard gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.
zh-cn: 指定照明对排行榜 GUI 的影响力值。值为 0 时完全熄灭，值为 1 时完全点亮。中间的分数值表示从完全熄灭到完全点亮之间的状态。

Source: Renders its contained GuiObjects flat against the face of a part.
en-us: Renders its contained GuiObjects flat against the face of a part.
zh-cn: 渲染其包含的平放在一个部件的面上的 GuiObject。

Source: The Object the surface gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.
en-us: The Object the surface gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.
zh-cn: 被此表面 GUI 用作渲染基础的 Object。目前只能通过脚本设置此属性，且必须存在于工作区。只有当指定对象派生自 BasePart 时才会进行渲染。

Source: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.
en-us: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.
zh-cn: 若值为 true，此 GuiObject 可触发鼠标事件并将其传递给下层 GuiObject，若值为 false 则无上述功能。

Source: If true, surface gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.
en-us: If true, surface gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.
zh-cn: 若值为 true，表面 GUI 会被渲染，否则将会跳过渲染。

Source: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the surface gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.
en-us: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the surface gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.
zh-cn: 指定照明对表面 GUI 的影响力值。值为 0 时完全熄灭，值为 1 时完全点亮。中间的分数值表示从完全熄灭到完全点亮之间的状态。

Source: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.
en-us: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.
zh-cn: 一个表明 GuiObject 在像素空间中的当前位置 (x, y) 的只读 Vector2 值，以 GuiObject 的左上角为准。

Source: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.
en-us: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.
zh-cn: 一个表明 GuiObject 在像素空间中的当前大小 (宽，高) 的只读 Vector2 值。

Source: An object that describes a particular user input, such as mouse movement, touches, keyboard, and more.
en-us: An object that describes a particular user input, such as mouse movement, touches, keyboard, and more.
zh-cn: 一个描述特定用户输入的对象，如鼠标移动、触碰、键盘等。

Source: An enum that describes what kind of input this object is describing (mousebutton, touch, etc.).  See Enum.UserInputType for more info.
en-us: An enum that describes what kind of input this object is describing (mousebutton, touch, etc.).  See Enum.UserInputType for more info.
zh-cn: 一个描述此对象描述的输入类型 (鼠标按钮、触碰等) 的枚举。更多信息请参阅 Enum.UserInputType。

Source: An enum that describes what state of a particular input (touch began, touch moved, touch ended, etc.). See Enum.UserInputState for more info.
en-us: An enum that describes what state of a particular input (touch began, touch moved, touch ended, etc.). See Enum.UserInputState for more info.
zh-cn: 一个描述特定输入的状态 (触碰开始、触碰移动、触碰结束等) 的枚举。更多信息请参阅 Enum.UserInputState。

Source: A Vector3 value that describes a positional value of this input. For mouse and touch input, this is the screen position of the mouse/touch, described in the x and y components. For mouse wheel input, the z component describes whether the wheel was moved forward or backward.
en-us: A Vector3 value that describes a positional value of this input. For mouse and touch input, this is the screen position of the mouse/touch, described in the x and y components. For mouse wheel input, the z component describes whether the wheel was moved forward or backward.
zh-cn: 一个描述此输入的位置值的 Vector3 值。针对鼠标和触碰输入，给出的是鼠标或触碰的屏幕位置，存放于 x 和 y 值中。针对鼠标滚轮输入， z 值描述滚轮的前滚或后滚。

Source: An enum that describes what kind of input is being pressed. For types of input like Keyboard, this describes what key was pressed. For input like mousebutton, this provides no additional information.
en-us: An enum that describes what kind of input is being pressed. For types of input like Keyboard, this describes what key was pressed. For input like mousebutton, this provides no additional information.
zh-cn: 一个描述此输入按键种类的枚举。针对键盘输入，描述按下的按键。针对鼠标按钮输入，不提供其他额外信息。

Source: Smoothly moves a GuiObject from its current position to 'endPosition'. The only required argument is 'endPosition'. More info
en-us: Smoothly moves a GuiObject from its current position to 'endPosition'. The only required argument is 'endPosition'. More info
zh-cn: 将一个 GuiObject 从当前位置平滑地移动至 'endPosition'。唯一的必要参数为 'endPosition'。更多信息

Source: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize'. The only required argument is 'endSize'. More info
en-us: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize'. The only required argument is 'endSize'. More info
zh-cn: 将一个 GuiObject 从当前大小平滑地形变至 'endSize'。唯一的必要参数为 'endSize'。更多信息

Source: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize', and also smoothly translates the GuiObject's current position to 'endPosition'. The only required arguments are 'endSize' and 'endPosition'. More info
en-us: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize', and also smoothly translates the GuiObject's current position to 'endPosition'. The only required arguments are 'endSize' and 'endPosition'. More info
zh-cn: 将一个 GuiObject 从当前大小平滑地形变至 'endSize'，并将其从当前位置平滑地移动至 'endPosition'。唯一的必要参数为 'endSize' 和 'endPosition'。更多信息

Source: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.
en-us: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.
zh-cn: 若值为 true，此 GuiObject 可触发鼠标事件并将其传递给下层 GuiObject，若值为 false 则无上述功能。

Source: A Color3 value that specifies the background color for the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
en-us: A Color3 value that specifies the background color for the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
zh-cn: 一个为 GuiObject 指定背景色的 Color3 值。若 Style 属性 (并非在所有 GuiObject 中都存在) 为非 Custom 的值，则此数值将被忽略。

Source: A number value that specifies how transparent the background of the GuiObject is. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
en-us: A number value that specifies how transparent the background of the GuiObject is. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
zh-cn: 一个为 GuiObject 指定背景透明度的数值。若 Style 属性 (并非在所有 GuiObject 中都存在) 为非 Custom 的值，则此数值将被忽略。

Source: A Color3 value that specifies the color of the outline of the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
en-us: A Color3 value that specifies the color of the outline of the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
zh-cn: 一个为 GuiObject 指定轮廓颜色的 Color3 值。若 Style 属性 (并非在所有 GuiObject 中都存在) 为非 Custom 的值，则此数值将被忽略。

Source: A number value that specifies the thickness (in pixels) of the outline of the GuiObject. Currently this value can only be set to either 0 or 1, any other number has no effect. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
en-us: A number value that specifies the thickness (in pixels) of the outline of the GuiObject. Currently this value can only be set to either 0 or 1, any other number has no effect. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.
zh-cn: 一个为 GuiObject 指定轮廓粗细的数值 (以像素为单位)。目前此值只能被设为 0 或 1，任何其他数字均无效。若 Style 属性 (并非在所有 GuiObject 中都存在) 为非 Custom 的值，则此数值将被忽略。

Source: If set to true, any descendants of this GuiObject will only render if contained within it's borders. If set to false, all descendants will render regardless of position.
en-us: If set to true, any descendants of this GuiObject will only render if contained within it's borders. If set to false, all descendants will render regardless of position.
zh-cn: 若值设为 true，此 GuiObject 的所有后代只有在其边框内才会被渲染。若值设为 false，所有后代无论位置均会被渲染。

Source: If true, allows a GuiObject to be dragged by the user's mouse. The events 'DragBegin' and 'DragStopped' are fired when the appropriate action happens, and only will fire on Draggable=true GuiObjects.
en-us: If true, allows a GuiObject to be dragged by the user's mouse. The events 'DragBegin' and 'DragStopped' are fired when the appropriate action happens, and only will fire on Draggable=true GuiObjects.
zh-cn: 若值为 true，允许 GuiObject 被用户的鼠标拖动。'DragBegin' 和 'DragStopped' 事件将会在相应操作发生时触发，且只会在 Draggable=true 的 GuiObject 上触发。

Source: A UDim2 value describing the size of the GuiObject on screen in both absolute and relative coordinates. More information on UDim2 is available here.
en-us: A UDim2 value describing the size of the GuiObject on screen in both absolute and relative coordinates. More information on UDim2 is available here.
zh-cn: 一个描述 GuiObject 在屏幕的绝对和相对坐标上的大小的 UDim2 值。更多关于 UDim2 的信息请参阅这里。

Source: A UDim2 value describing the position of the top-left corner of the GuiObject on screen. More information on UDim2 is available here.
en-us: A UDim2 value describing the position of the top-left corner of the GuiObject on screen. More information on UDim2 is available here.
zh-cn: 一个描述 GuiObject 的左上角在屏幕上的位置的 UDim2 值。更多关于 UDim2 的信息请参阅这里。"

Source: The direction(s) that an object can be resized in. More info.
en-us: The direction(s) that an object can be resized in. More info.
zh-cn: 对象可以调整大小的方向。更多信息。

Source: Describes the ordering in which overlapping GuiObjects will be drawn. A value of 1 is drawn first, while higher values are drawn in ascending order (each value draws over the last).
en-us: Describes the ordering in which overlapping GuiObjects will be drawn. A value of 1 is drawn first, while higher values are drawn in ascending order (each value draws over the last).
zh-cn: 描述绘制 GuiObject 的叠加顺序。值为 1 时首先绘制，后续按值的升序依次绘制 (较大的值绘制在较小的值上方)。

Source: Deprecated. Use BackgroundColor3 instead
en-us: Deprecated. Use BackgroundColor3 instead
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 BackgroundColor3

Source: Deprecated. Use BorderColor3 instead
en-us: Deprecated. Use BorderColor3 instead
zh-cn: 已过时。请改用 BorderColor3

Source: Overrides the default selection adornment (used for gamepads). For best results, this should point to a GuiObject.
en-us: Overrides the default selection adornment (used for gamepads). For best results, this should point to a GuiObject.
zh-cn: 覆盖默认选择装饰 (用于游戏手柄)。为了获得最佳效果，应指向一个 GuiObject。

Source: Fired when a GuiObject with Draggable set to true starts to be dragged. 'InitialPosition' is a UDim2 value of the position of the GuiObject before any drag operation began.
en-us: Fired when a GuiObject with Draggable set to true starts to be dragged. 'InitialPosition' is a UDim2 value of the position of the GuiObject before any drag operation began.
zh-cn: Draggable 设为 true 的 GuiObject 被拖动时触发。'InitialPosition' 是一个记录 GuiObject 在拖动开始前位置的 UDim2 值。

Source: Always fired after a DragBegin event, DragStopped is fired when the user releases the mouse button causing a drag operation on the GuiObject. Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the top-left absolute position of the GuiObject when the event is fired.
en-us: Always fired after a DragBegin event, DragStopped is fired when the user releases the mouse button causing a drag operation on the GuiObject. Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the top-left absolute position of the GuiObject when the event is fired.
zh-cn: 总是在 DragBegin 事件后触发。DragStopped 在用户松开导致 GuiObject 拖动操作的鼠标按键后触发。参数 'x' 和 'y' 指定事件触发时 GuiObject 左上角的绝对位置。

Source: Fired when the mouse enters a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.
en-us: Fired when the mouse enters a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.
zh-cn: 只要 GuiObject 处于活跃状态 (参阅活跃属性了解更多详细信息)，当鼠标进入 GuiObject 时触发。参数 'x' 和 'y' 指定鼠标的绝对像素位置。

Source: Fired when the mouse leaves a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.
en-us: Fired when the mouse leaves a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.
zh-cn: 只要 GuiObject 处于活跃状态 (参阅活跃属性了解更多详细信息)，但鼠标离开 GuiObject 时触发。参数 'x' 和 'y' 指定鼠标的绝对像素位置。

Source: Fired when the mouse is inside a GuiObject and moves, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.
en-us: Fired when the mouse is inside a GuiObject and moves, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.
zh-cn: 只要 GuiObject 处于活跃状态 (参阅活跃属性了解更多详细信息)，当鼠标在 GuiObject 内移动时触发。参数 'x' 和 'y' 指定鼠标的绝对像素位置。

Source: Fired when a user taps their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the tap gesture. This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
en-us: Fired when a user taps their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the tap gesture. This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.
zh-cn: 当用户在 TouchEnabled 设备上轻触手指时触发。 'touchPositions' 是一个 Vector2 的 Lua 数组，其成员各自代表轻触手势中涉及的所有手指的位置。此事件仅在本地触发。无论游戏状态如何，此事件总是会触发。

Source: Fired when a user pinches their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the pinch gesture. 'scale' is a float that indicates the difference from the beginning of the pinch gesture. 'velocity' is a float indicating how quickly the pinch gesture is happening. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
en-us: Fired when a user pinches their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the pinch gesture. 'scale' is a float that indicates the difference from the beginning of the pinch gesture. 'velocity' is a float indicating how quickly the pinch gesture is happening. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
zh-cn: 当用户在启用 TouchEnabled 的设备上捏合手指时触发。'touchPositions' 是一个 Vector2 Lua 数组，其成员各自代表捏合手势中所涉及的全部手指的位置。 'scale' 是一个代表从捏合手势开始的差异值的浮点数。'velocity' 是一个代表捏合手势发生速度的浮点数。'state' 代表手势的 the Enum.UserInputState。此事件仅在本地触发。

Source: Fired when a user swipes their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'swipeDirection' is an Enum.SwipeDirection, indicating the direction the user swiped. 'numberOfTouches' is an int that indicates how many touches were involved with the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
en-us: Fired when a user swipes their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'swipeDirection' is an Enum.SwipeDirection, indicating the direction the user swiped. 'numberOfTouches' is an int that indicates how many touches were involved with the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
zh-cn: 当用户在启用 TouchEnabled 的设备上滑动手指时触发。'swipeDirection' 是一个代表用户滑动方向的 Enum.SwipeDirection。 'numberOfTouches' 是一个代表该手势中涉及的触碰数量的整数。此事件仅在本地触发。

Source: Fired when a user holds at least one finger for a short amount of time on the same screen position on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
en-us: Fired when a user holds at least one finger for a short amount of time on the same screen position on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
zh-cn: 当用户在启用 TouchEnabled 的设备上用至少一根手指在同一屏幕位置短暂停留时触发。'touchPositions' 是一个 Vector2 Lua 数组，其成员各自代表该手势中涉及的所有手指的位置。'state' 代表手势的 Enum.UserInputState。此事件仅在本地触发。

Source: Fired when a user rotates two fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'rotation' is a float indicating how much the rotation has gone from the start of the gesture. 'velocity' is a float that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
en-us: Fired when a user rotates two fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'rotation' is a float indicating how much the rotation has gone from the start of the gesture. 'velocity' is a float that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.
zh-cn: 当用户在启用 TouchEnabled 的设备上旋转两根手指时触发。'touchPositions' 是一个 Vector2 Lua 数组，其成员各自代表该手势中涉及的所有手指的位置。'rotation' 是一个代表手势从初始位置旋转角度的浮点数。'velocity' 是一个代表旋转手势发生速度的浮点数。'state' 代表手势的 Enum.UserInputState。此事件仅在本地触发。

Source: Fired when a user drags at least one finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'totalTranslation' is a Vector2, indicating how far the pan gesture has gone from its starting point. 'velocity' is a Vector2 that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed in each dimension. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.
en-us: Fired when a user drags at least one finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'totalTranslation' is a Vector2, indicating how far the pan gesture has gone from its starting point. 'velocity' is a Vector2 that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed in each dimension. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.
zh-cn: 当用户在启用 TouchEnabled 的设备上拖动至少一根手指时触发。'touchPositions' 是一个 Vector2 Lua 数组，其成员各自代表该手势中涉及的所有手指的位置。'totalTranslation' 是一个 Vector2，代表拖动手势从初始位置所行进的距离。'velocity' 是一个代表手势在各维度上行进速度的 Vector2。'state' 代表手势的 Enum.UserInputState。

Source: Fired when a user begins interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button down, touch begin, keyboard button down, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.
en-us: Fired when a user begins interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button down, touch begin, keyboard button down, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.
zh-cn: 当用户开始通过人机交互设备进行交互 (按下鼠标按钮、触碰开始、按下键盘按键等) 时触发。'inputObject' 是一个包含查询用户输入的有用数据的 InputObject。此事件仅在本地触发。

Source: Fired when a user changes interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse move, touch move, mouse wheel, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.
en-us: Fired when a user changes interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse move, touch move, mouse wheel, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.
zh-cn: 当用户通过人机交互设备变更交互 (鼠标移动、触碰移动、鼠标滚轮等) 时触发。'inputObject' 是一个包含查询用户输入的有用数据的 InputObject。此事件仅在本地触发。

Source: Fired when a user stops interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button up, touch end, keyboard button up, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.
en-us: Fired when a user stops interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button up, touch end, keyboard button up, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.
zh-cn: 当用户停止通过人机交互设备进行交互 (松开鼠标按钮、触碰结束、松开键盘按键等) 时触发。'inputObject' 是一个包含查询用户输入的有用数据的 InputObject。此事件仅在本地触发。

Source: A container object used to layout other GUI objects
en-us: A container object used to layout other GUI objects
zh-cn: 用于布局其他 GUI 对象的容器对象

Source: Determines how a frame will look. Uses Enum.FrameStyle. More info
en-us: Determines how a frame will look. Uses Enum.FrameStyle. More info
zh-cn: 决定框架的外观。使用 Enum.FrameStyle。更多信息

Source: Studio.App.RobloxRibbonMainWindow.ScrollingFrameTooltip
en-us: Studio.App.RobloxRibbonMainWindow.ScrollingFrameTooltip
zh-cn: Studio.App.RobloxRibbonMainWindow.ScrollingFrameTooltip

Source: Determines whether or not scrolling is allowed on this frame. If turned off, no scroll bars will be rendered.
en-us: Determines whether or not scrolling is allowed on this frame. If turned off, no scroll bars will be rendered.
zh-cn: 决定此框架内是否允许滚动。若禁用，将不会渲染滚动条。

Source: Determines the size of the area that is scrollable. The UDim2 is calculated using the parent gui's size, similar to the regular Size property on gui objects.
en-us: Determines the size of the area that is scrollable. The UDim2 is calculated using the parent gui's size, similar to the regular Size property on gui objects.
zh-cn: 决定可滚动的区域大小。使用父 GUI 的大小计算 UDim2，类似 GUI 对象的常规 Size 属性。

Source: The absolute position the scroll frame is in respect to the canvas size. The minimum this can be set to is (0,0), while the max is the absolute canvas size - AbsoluteWindowSize.
en-us: The absolute position the scroll frame is in respect to the canvas size. The minimum this can be set to is (0,0), while the max is the absolute canvas size - AbsoluteWindowSize.
zh-cn: 滚动框架相对画布大小的绝对位置。最小值可设为 (0,0)，最大值为画布的绝对尺寸 - AbsoluteWindowSize。

Source: The size in pixels of the frame, without the scrollbars.
en-us: The size in pixels of the frame, without the scrollbars.
zh-cn: 框架的尺寸，以像素为单位，滚动条不计入内。

Source: How thick the scroll bar appears. This applies to both the horizontal and vertical scroll bars. Can be set to 0 for no bars render.
en-us: How thick the scroll bar appears. This applies to both the horizontal and vertical scroll bars. Can be set to 0 for no bars render.
zh-cn: 滚动条的厚度。同样适用于水平和垂直滚动条。设为 0 则不渲染滚动条。

Source: The "Up" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the "left" image on the horizontal scroll bar.
en-us: The "Up" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the "left" image on the horizontal scroll bar.
zh-cn: 垂直滚动条的“上”图像。大小始终为 ScrollBarThickness x ScrollBarThickness。还可以作为水平滚动条的“左”图像。

Source: The "Middle" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this can vary in the y direction, but is always set at ScrollBarThickness in x direction. This is also used as the "mid" image on the horizontal scroll bar.
en-us: The "Middle" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this can vary in the y direction, but is always set at ScrollBarThickness in x direction. This is also used as the "mid" image on the horizontal scroll bar.
zh-cn: 垂直滚动条的“中间”图像。此图像的大小可以在 y 轴产生变化，但在 x 轴方向上其值应始终为 ScrollBarThickness。还可以作为水平滚动条的“中间”图像。

Source: The "Down" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the "right" image on the horizontal scroll bar.
en-us: The "Down" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the "right" image on the horizontal scroll bar.
zh-cn: 垂直滚动条的“下”图像。大小始终为 ScrollBarThickness x ScrollBarThickness。还可以作为水平滚动条的“右”图像。

en-us: A GUI object containing an Image
zh-cn: 包含图片的 GUI 对象

Source: Specifies the id of the texture to display. More info
en-us: Specifies the id of the texture to display. More info
zh-cn: 指定要显示的纹理的 ID。更多信息

Source: Specifies how an image should be displayed. See ScaleType for more info.
en-us: Specifies how an image should be displayed. See ScaleType for more info.
zh-cn: 指定图片的显示方式。更多信息请参阅 ScaleType。

Source: If ScaleType is set to Slice, this Rect is used to specify the central part of the image. Everything outside of this is considered to be the border.
en-us: If ScaleType is set to Slice, this Rect is used to specify the central part of the image. Everything outside of this is considered to be the border.
zh-cn: 若 ScaleType 设为 Slice，此 Rect 用于指定图片的中心部分。除此以外的一切均被视为边缘。

Source: If ScaleType is set to Tile, this sets the size of the tile.
en-us: If ScaleType is set to Tile, this sets the size of the tile.
zh-cn: 若 ScaleType 设为 Tile，此项将设置地砖的大小。

Source: Determines whether a button changes color automatically when reacting to mouse events.
en-us: Determines whether a button changes color automatically when reacting to mouse events.
zh-cn: 决定一个按钮在响应鼠标事件时是否自动改变颜色。

Source: Allows the mouse to be free in first person mode. If a button with this property set to true is visible, the mouse is 'free' in first person mode.
en-us: Allows the mouse to be free in first person mode. If a button with this property set to true is visible, the mouse is 'free' in first person mode.
zh-cn: 允许鼠标在第一人称模式下自由移动。若一个此属性被设为 true，则按钮可见，鼠标也可以在第一人称模式下“自由”移动。

Source: Determines how a button will look, including mouse event states. Uses Enum.ButtonStyle. More info
en-us: Determines how a button will look, including mouse event states. Uses Enum.ButtonStyle. More info
zh-cn: 决定一个按钮的外观，包括鼠标事件状态。使用 Enum.ButtonStyle。更多信息

Source: Fired when the mouse is over the button, and the mouse down and up events fire without the mouse leaving the button.
en-us: Fired when the mouse is over the button, and the mouse down and up events fire without the mouse leaving the button.
zh-cn: 当鼠标悬停在按钮上且未离开按钮，鼠标键按下和松开事件触发时触发。

Source: Fired when the mouse button is pushed down on a button.
en-us: Fired when the mouse button is pushed down on a button.
zh-cn: 当鼠标键按下按钮时触发。

Source: Fired when the mouse button is released on a button.
en-us: Fired when the mouse button is released on a button.
zh-cn: 当鼠标键从按钮上松开时触发。

Source: Specifies how an image should be displayed. See ScaleType for more info.

Source: If ScaleType is set to Slice, this Rect is used to specify the central part of the image. Everything outside of this is considered to be the border.
en-us: If ScaleType is set to Slice, this Rect is used to specify the central part of the image. Everything outside of this is considered to be the border.
zh-cn: 若 ScaleType 设为 Slice，此 Rect 用于指定图片的中心部分。除此以外的一切均被视为边缘。

en-us: A visual line drawn representation between two part objects
zh-cn: 两个部件对象之间绘制可视线表示

en-us: A visual line drawn representation between two positions

en-us: The pose of a joint relative to it's parent part in a keyframe
zh-cn: 接头在关键帧中相对其父部件的姿态

Source: Represents when an event should be fired in an animation
en-us: Represents when an event should be fired in an animation
zh-cn: 代表一个事件应该在动画中触发

Source: One keyframe of an animation
en-us: One keyframe of an animation
zh-cn: 动画的一个关键帧

Source: Represents a linked animation object, containing keyframes and poses.
en-us: Represents a linked animation object, containing keyframes and poses.
zh-cn: 代表一个关联动画对象，包含关键帧和姿态。

Source: Returned by a call to LoadAnimation. Controls the playback of an animation on a Humanoid.
en-us: Returned by a call to LoadAnimation. Controls the playback of an animation on a Humanoid.
zh-cn: 通过调用 LoadAnimation 返回。控制 Humanoid 上动画的播放。

Source: Allows animations to be played on joints of the parent object.
en-us: Allows animations to be played on joints of the parent object.

Source: An object used to make dialog trees to converse with players
en-us: An object used to make dialog trees to converse with players
zh-cn: 用于创建对话框树与玩家交谈的对象

Source: The maximum distance that the player's character can be from the dialog's parent in order to use the dialog.
en-us: The maximum distance that the player's character can be from the dialog's parent in order to use the dialog.
zh-cn: 玩家角色使用对话框时与对话框父类的最远距离。

Source: Indicates whether or not an extra choice is available for the player to exit the dialog tree at this node.
en-us: Indicates whether or not an extra choice is available for the player to exit the dialog tree at this node.
zh-cn: 表明是否有额外的选项让玩家在此节点退出对话框树。

Source: The prompt text for an extra choice that allows the player to exit the dialog tree at this node.
en-us: The prompt text for an extra choice that allows the player to exit the dialog tree at this node.

Source: Indicates whether or not the dialog is currently being used by one or more players.
en-us: Indicates whether or not the dialog is currently being used by one or more players.
zh-cn: 表明对话框当前是否正被一个或以上玩家使用。

Source: The chat message that is displayed to the player when they first activate the dialog.
en-us: The chat message that is displayed to the player when they first activate the dialog.
zh-cn: 玩家首次激活对话框时向其显示的聊天信息。

Source: Describes the purpose of the dialog, which is used to display a relevant icon on the dialog's activation button.
en-us: Describes the purpose of the dialog, which is used to display a relevant icon on the dialog's activation button.
zh-cn: 描述对话框的用途，用于在对话框的激活按钮上显示相关图标。

Source: Describes the tone of the dialog, which is used to display a relevant color in the dialog interface.
en-us: Describes the tone of the dialog, which is used to display a relevant color in the dialog interface.
zh-cn: 描述对话框的语气，用于在对话框界面显示相关颜色。

Source: Indicates how the dialog may be used by players. Use Enum.DialogBehaviorType.SinglePlayer if only one player should interact with the dialog at a time, otherwise use Enum.DialogBehaviorType.MultiplePlayers.
en-us: Indicates how the dialog may be used by players. Use Enum.DialogBehaviorType.SinglePlayer if only one player should interact with the dialog at a time, otherwise use Enum.DialogBehaviorType.MultiplePlayers.
zh-cn: 表明玩家使用对话框的方式。若同一时间内只有一名玩家能与对话框互动，请使用 Enum.DialogBehaviorType.SinglePlayer，否则使用 Enum.DialogBehaviorType.MultiplePlayers。

Source: Returns an array of the players currently conversing with this dialog.

Source: If 'functionToBind' from ContextActionService:BindAction() returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Sink, the input event will stop at that function and no other bound actions under it will be invoked. This is the default behavior if 'functionToBind' does not return anything or yields in any way.
en-us: If 'functionToBind' from ContextActionService:BindAction() returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Sink, the input event will stop at that function and no other bound actions under it will be invoked. This is the default behavior if 'functionToBind' does not return anything or yields in any way.
zh-cn: 若 ContextActionService:BindAction() 的 'functionToBind' 返回 Enum.ContextActionResult.Sink，则输入事件在该函数处停止，且不会调用其下的其他绑定操作。此行为是 'functionToBind' 未返回内容或因任意方式而暂停时的默认行为。

Source: If 'functionToBind' from ContextActionService:BindAction() returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Pass, the input event is considered to have not been handled by 'functionToBind' and will continue being passed to actions bound to the same input type.
en-us: If 'functionToBind' from ContextActionService:BindAction() returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Pass, the input event is considered to have not been handled by 'functionToBind' and will continue being passed to actions bound to the same input type.
zh-cn: 若 ContextActionService:BindAction() 的 'functionToBind' 返回 Enum.ContextActionResult.Pass，则输入事件被视为未经 'functionToBind' 处理，并将继续传递给绑定至相同输入类型的操作。

en-us: The ordering to use for sorting an array of GuiObjects.

en-us: Sort by alphabetical ordering of the Name property.
zh-cn: 根据 Name 属性的字母顺序进行排序。

en-us: Sort using the less than operator on the LayoutOrder property of GuiObject.
zh-cn: 使用 GuiObject 的 LayoutOrder 属性的小于运算符进行排序。

Source: Controls the behavior of the ZIndex property.
en-us: Controls the behavior of the ZIndex property.
zh-cn: 控制 ZIndex 属性的行为。

Source: The ZIndex property will override the default value computed from the depth in the hierarchy.
en-us: The ZIndex property will override the default value computed from the depth in the hierarchy.
zh-cn: ZIndex 属性会覆盖由层次结构底层计算得出的默认值。

Source: The ZIndex property will control the order that the GuiObject will be rendered relative to its siblings.
en-us: The ZIndex property will control the order that the GuiObject will be rendered relative to its siblings.
zh-cn: ZIndex 属性会控制 GuiObject 相对其同级的渲染顺序。

Source: Controls how an image is displayed.
en-us: Controls how an image is displayed.
zh-cn: 控制图像的显示方式。

Source: Force the image to fill the available space.
en-us: Force the image to fill the available space.
zh-cn: 强制使用图像填充可用空间。

Source: Use the SliceCenter property to stretch the middle of the image but maintain crisp borders.
en-us: Use the SliceCenter property to stretch the middle of the image but maintain crisp borders.
zh-cn: 使用 SliceCenter 属性拉伸图像中央但维持清晰边缘。

Source: Tile the image using the TileSize property.
en-us: Tile the image using the TileSize property.
zh-cn: 使用 TileSize 属性平铺图像。

Source: Size the image to the largest size that will fit in the available space while maintaining aspect ratio.
en-us: Size the image to the largest size that will fit in the available space while maintaining aspect ratio.
zh-cn: 将图像调整为适合可用空间的最大尺寸，同时保持宽高比。

Source: Fill the available space, maintaining aspect ratio by cropping the edges if necessary.
en-us: Fill the available space, maintaining aspect ratio by cropping the edges if necessary.
zh-cn: 填充可用空间，必要时通过裁剪边缘来维持宽高比。

Source: A container instance that contains Scripts.  Useful only for Plugins.  When Studio starts, we load plugins into the 'UserPlugin' data model and execute Scripts contained in StandalonePluginScripts container. If a plugin doesn't have such a container then the plugin isn't loaded into UserPlugin data model.  When a data model for a place is created (e.g. the Edit data model), we load plugins into said data model and execute only those Scripts which are not contained in StandalonePluginScripts container.
en-us: A container instance that contains Scripts.  Useful only for Plugins.  When Studio starts, we load plugins into the 'UserPlugin' data model and execute Scripts contained in StandalonePluginScripts container. If a plugin doesn't have such a container then the plugin isn't loaded into UserPlugin data model.  When a data model for a place is created (e.g. the Edit data model), we load plugins into said data model and execute only those Scripts which are not contained in StandalonePluginScripts container.
zh-cn: 一个包含 Script 的容器实例。仅适合配合插件使用。当 Studio 启动后，我们会将插件载入 'UserPlugin' 数据模型并执行包含在 StandalonePluginScripts 容器中的 Script。若某个插件不包含此容器，则插件不会被载入 UserPlugin 数据模型。在创建一个场景的数据模型（如 Edit 数据模型）后，我们会将插件载入上述数据模型并只执行未包含在 StandalonePluginScripts 容器中的 Script。
